#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:933
msgid ""
"Slight tweak to the pipebackend to ease DNSSEC operations (c2239, "
"c2247). Also fix pipebackend support in pdnssec tool (c2244)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:938
msgid ""
"Upgrade the experimental native Lua backend to the latest version from "
"Fredrik Danerklint (c2240) and include this backend in the .deb packages "
"(c2242)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:943
msgid ""
"Remove IPv6 dependency, it was only possible to run master/slave operations "
"on a server with at least one IPv6 address. Some very old virtualized setups "
"turned out to have no IPv6 at all. Fix in c2246."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:954
msgid ""
"PowerDNS Authoritative Server could not be configured to use an IPv6 based "
"resolving backend. Solved in c2191."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:959
msgid ""
"LDAP backend reconfigured the timezone (TZ) setting of the daemon, leading "
"to confusing logfile entries. Fixed by Christian Hofstaedtler in c2913, "
"closing t313."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:965
msgid ""
"Non-DNSSEC capable backends could crash on DNSSEC queries. Fixed in c2194 "
"and c2196 (thanks to Charlie Smurthwaite) closing t360."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:970
msgid ""
"Errors looking up a UID or GID were reported confusingly ('Success'), fixed "
"in c2195, closing t359."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:975
msgid ""
"Fix compilation against older MySQL, client libraries (c2198, c2199, c2204), "
"especially for older RHEL/CentOS. Also addresses the failure to look in "
"lib64 directory for PostgreSQL."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:981
msgid ""
"Sqlite3 needs write access not just to its database file, but also to the "
"directory it is in. If this wasn't the case, no useful error message was "
"provided. Improvement in c2202."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:987
msgid "Update of MongoDB backend (c2203, c2212)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:992
msgid ""
"'pdnssec hash-zone-record' emitted an inverted warning about narrow NSEC3 "
"hashes. Spotted by Jan-Piet Mens, fix in c2205."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:997
msgid ""
"PowerDNS can fill out default fields for SOA records, but neglected to do so "
"if the SOA record was matched by an incoming ANY question.  Spotted by Marc "
"Laros &amp; others. Fixes t357, code in c2206."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1003
msgid ""
"PowerDNS would mistreat binary data in TXT records. Fix in c2207. Again "
"spotted by Jan-Piet Mens. Closes t356."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1008
msgid ""
"Add experimental Lua backend by our star contributor Fredrik "
"Danerklint. c2208."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1013
msgid ""
"Christoph Meerwald discovered our RRSIG freshness checking checked more than "
"the intended RRSIG (on the SOA record). Fix in c2209."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1018
msgid ""
"Christoph Meerwald discovered we got confused by TSIG signed EDNS-adorned "
"queries, since we expected the EDNS OPT pseudorecord to be the very last "
"record. Fix in c2214."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1024
msgid ""
"Christoph Meerwald discovered that when using SOA outgoing editing we would "
"sign and THEN edit. This was not productive. Fixed in c2215."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1029
msgid ""
"Add missing-but-documented pdnssec command 'disable-dnssec'. Spotted by "
"Craig Whitmore. Plus fixed misleading --help output. Code in c2216."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1034
msgid ""
"By popular demand, a tweak which makes an overloaded database no longer "
"restart PowerDNS but to drop queries until the database is available again.  "
"Code in c2217, lightly tested. Enable by setting 'overload-queue-length=100' "
"(for example)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1040
msgid ""
"By suggestion of Miek Gieben of SIDN, add SOA-EDIT mode 'EPOCH' which sets "
"the SOA serial number to the 'UNIX time'. Implemented in c2218."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1046
msgid ""
"Added some US export control &amp; ECCN to documentation, needed because of "
"DNSSEC content. Update in c2219."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1051
msgid ""
"Fix up various spelling mistakes and badly formatted messages (c2220 and "
"c2221) by Maik Zumstrull and 'anonymous'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1056
msgid ""
"After a lot of thought, we now handle CNAMEs to names outside our knowledge "
"('bailiwick') exactly as in BIND 9.8.0, even though our way was standards "
"compliant too. It confused things. Update in c2222 and c2224."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1062
msgid ""
"Tweak sqlite3 library location detection for newer Ubuntu versions. Change "
"in c2223."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1067
msgid ""
"DNSSEC SQL schema improvements allowing for the use of constraints and "
"foreign keys in c2225, by Gerald Gruenberg, closing t371."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1072
msgid ""
"Add support for EDNS option 'edns-subnet', based on "
"draft-vandergaast-edns-client-subnet (c2226, c2228, c2229, c2230, c2231, "
"c2233)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1077
msgid ""
"Silence SIGCHLD warning from Perl when used to power 'pipe' backends "
"(c2232)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1082
msgid ""
"Add experimental support, off by default, for draft-edns-subnet.  See c2233 "
"and c2239 for details how to use this feature."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1090
msgid ""
"PostgreSQL and LDAP backends can now deal with a restart of their respective "
"servers. Many thanks to Peter van Dijk for debugging and Nikolaos Milas for "
"supplying a reproduction path of the problem (&amp; much nagging). Fixes in "
"c2233 and c2235."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1100
msgid ""
"Jan-Piet Mens discovered that records inserted by Lua on zone retrieval did "
"not get correct 'ordername' and 'auth' fields for DNSSEC.  Fixed in c2174."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1106
msgid ""
"Silenced various relevant and less relevant compilation warnings "
"(c2175). Thanks to Serge Belyshev for pointing out the error in our ways."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1112
msgid ""
"Steve Bauer discovered we would cache empty recursive answers in some "
"cases. Addressed in c2176."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1117
msgid ""
"James Cloos reported that 'pdnssec check-zone' tripped over SRV "
"records. Fixed this, and added check-zone to the regression tests.  Code in "
"c2177."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1123
msgid ""
"DNSSEC regression tests were added in commits C2178, C2179, C2182, C2186 We "
"test against the fine tools from NLNetLabs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1128
msgid ""
"Secure DNSSEC delegations to ourselves picked wrong zone to serve the DS "
"record from. Fixed in c2180, c2181, c2183.  reported by Niek Willems of "
"InterNLnet."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1134
msgid ""
"Stef Van Dessel suggested we made our RPMs state explicitly that they need "
"glibc 2.4 on Linux. Code in c2184."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1139
msgid ""
"John Leach discovered our MySQL based backends would wait for ages on a "
"failing MySQL server.  The patch merged in c2189 reduces the timeout "
"significantly, which is especially useful with haproxy and mysqlproxy."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1145
msgid ""
"c2190 fixes a crash reported by Marc Laros when using a non-DNSSEC capable "
"backend. Should also improve non-DNSSEC performance."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1155
msgid ""
"Zone2sql sent out the wrong 'COMMIT' statement in sqlite mode. In addition, "
"in this mode, zone2sql would not emit statements to update the domains table "
"unless the 'slave' setting was chosen. Code in c2167."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1161
msgid ""
"We dropped the Authoritative Answer flag on an out-of-bailiwick CNAME "
"referral, which was unnecessary. Code in c2170."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1166
msgid ""
"Kees Monshouwer discovered that we failed to detect the location of "
"PostgreSQL on RHEL/CentOS. Fix in c2144. In addition, c2162 eases detection "
"of MySQL on RHEL/CentOS 64 bits systems."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1172
msgid ""
"Marc Laros re-reported an old bug in the internally used 'pdns' backend "
"where details of the SOA record were not filled out correctly.  Resolved in "
"c2145."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1178
msgid ""
"Jan-Piet Mens found that our TSIG signed SOA zone freshness check was signed "
"incorrectly. Fixed in c2147. Improved error messages that helped debug this "
"issue in c2148, c2149."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1184
msgid ""
"Jan-Piet Mens helped debug an issue where some servers were \"almost "
"always\" unable to transfer a TSIG signed zone correctly.  Turns out that "
"the TSIG signing code used an internal timestamp and not the remote "
"timestamp. Because of good NTP synchronization this quite often was not a "
"problem. Fix in c2159."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1191
msgid ""
"Thor Spruyt of Telenet discovered that the PowerDNS code would try to emit "
"DNS answers over TCP of over 65535 bytes long, which failed.  We now "
"truncate such answers properly. Code in c2150."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1197
msgid ""
"The Slave engine now reuses an existing database connection, removing the "
"need to create a new database connection every minute (and worse, log about "
"it).  Code in c2153."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1203
msgid ""
"Fix a potential Year 2106 bug in the TSIG signing code. Because we care "
"(c2156)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1208
msgid ""
"Added experimental support for the 'DANE' TLSA record which is used to "
"authenticate SSL certificates via DNSSEC. c2161."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1213
msgid ""
"Added experimental support for the MongoDB 'NoSQL' backend, contributed by "
"Fredrik Danerklint in c2162."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1219
msgid "On to the release notes. Next to DNSSEC, other major new features include:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1225
msgid ""
"TSIG for authorizing and authenticating AXFR requests &amp; incoming zone "
"transfers (Code in C2024, C2025, C2033, C2034).  This allows for retrieving "
"TSIG protected content, as well as serving it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1231
msgid "Per zone also-notify."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1236
msgid ""
"MyDNS compatible backend, allowing for 'instantaneous' migration from this "
"authoritative nameserver. Code in c1418, contributed by Jonathan Oddy."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1242
msgid ""
"PowerDNS can now slave zones over IPv6 and notify IPv6 remotes of "
"updates. Already. Code in c2009 and beyond."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1247
msgid ""
"Lua based incoming zone editing, allowing masters or signing slaves to add "
"information to the zone they will (re-)serve. Implemented in c2065. To "
"enable, use LUA-AXFR-SCRIPT zone metadata setting."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1253
msgid ""
"Native Oracle backend with full DNSSEC support. Contributed by Maik "
"Zumstrull, then at the Steinbuch Centre for Computing at the Karlsruhe "
"Institute of Technology."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1259
msgid ""
"\"Also-notify\" support, implemented by Aki Tuomi in c1400. Support for "
"Generic SQL backends and for the BIND backend. Further code in c1360."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1265
msgid "Support for binding to thousands of IP addresses, code in c1443."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1270
msgid ""
"Generic MySQL backend now supports stored procedures. Implemented in c2084, "
"closing t231."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1275
msgid ""
"Generic ODBC backend compiles again, and is reported to work for some users "
"that need it. Code contributed in t309, author unknown."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1281
msgid ""
"Massively parallel slaving infrastructure, able to check the freshness of "
"thousands of remote zones per second, plus perform many incoming zone "
"transfers simultaneously. Sponsored by Tyler Hall, code in C1449, C1500, "
"C1859"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1289
msgid ""
"Core DNS logic replaced completely to deal with the brave new world of "
"DNSSEC."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1294 docs/pdns.xml:2351 docs/pdns.xml:4309 docs/pdns.xml:5398 docs/pdns.xml:5553 docs/pdns.xml:6190 docs/pdns.xml:6587 docs/pdns.xml:6756 docs/pdns.xml:6847 docs/pdns.xml:6891 docs/pdns.xml:6941 docs/pdns.xml:7018 docs/pdns.xml:7146 docs/pdns.xml:7268 docs/pdns.xml:7395 docs/pdns.xml:7483 docs/pdns.xml:7567 docs/pdns.xml:7671 docs/pdns.xml:7783 docs/pdns.xml:7869
msgid "Bugs fixed:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1298
msgid ""
"sqlite2 and sqlite3 backends used MySQL-style escaping, leading to SQL "
"errors in some cases. Discovered by Sten Spans. Fixed in c1342."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1304
msgid ""
"Internal webserver no longer prints '1e2%'. Bug rediscovered by Jeff "
"Sipek. Fixed in c1342."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1309
msgid ""
"PowerDNS would refuse to serve domain names with spaces in them, or "
"otherwise non-printable characters. Addressed in c2081."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1315
msgid ""
"PowerDNS can now serve escaped labels, as described by RFC 4343. Data should "
"be present in backends in that escaped form. Code in c2089."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1321
msgid ""
"In some cases, we would include duplicate CNAMEs. In addition, we would hand "
"out a full root-referral when not configured to in some cases (ticket "
"t223). Discovered by Andreas Jakum, fixed in c1344."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1327
msgid ""
"Shane Kerr discovered we would corrupt DNS transaction IDs from the packet "
"cache on big endian systems.  Fix in c1346, closing t222."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1333
msgid ""
"PowerDNS did not use RFC 1982 serial arithmetic, leading to a SOA serial "
"number of 1 to be regarded as older than 4400000000, when in fact it is "
"'newer'. Issue (re-)discovered by Jan-Piet Mens."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1339
msgid ""
"BIND backend got confused of a zone's file name changed after a "
"configuration reload.  Fix in c1347, closing t228."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1345
msgid ""
"When restarted by the Guardian, PowerDNS will perform a full multi-threaded "
"cache cleanup, which took a long time and could crash. Fix in c1364."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1351
msgid ""
"Under artificial circumstances, PowerDNS would never clean its packet "
"cache. Found by Marcus Goller, fix in c1399 and c1408. This update also "
"retunes the cleanup frequency."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1357
msgid ""
"Packetcache would cache things it should not have been caching. Fixes in "
"commits C1407, C1488, C1869, C1880"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1362
msgid ""
"When processing incoming notifications, the BIND backend was case-sensitive, "
"and would disregard notifications in the wrong case. Discovered by "
"'Dolphin', fix in c1420."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1368
msgid ""
"The init.d script did not mention the 'reload' command. Code in c1463, "
"closes t233."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1373
msgid ""
"Generic SQL Backends would sometimes emit obscure error messages. Fix in "
"c2049."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1379
msgid ""
"PowerDNS would be confused by embedded NULs in domain names, and would also "
"mess up the escaping of some characters. Fix in c1468, c1469, c1478, c1480,"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1385
msgid ""
"SOA queries for the name of a delegation point were not referred. Fix in "
"c1466, closing t224.  In addition, queries for AAAA for a CNAMEd record "
"pointing to a name with no AAAA would deliver a direct SOA, without the "
"CNAME in between. Fix in c1542, c1607.  Also, wildcard CNAMEs pointing to a "
"record without the type requested suffered from the same issue, fix in "
"c1543."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1393
msgid ""
"On processing an incoming AXFR, once an MX or SRV record had been seen, all "
"future fields got a 'priority' entry as well. This had no operational "
"impact, but looked messy. Fixed in c1437."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1399
msgid ""
"Aki Tuomi discovered that the BIND zone file parser would misrepresent "
"'something IN MX 15 @'. Fix in c1621."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1404
msgid ""
"Marco Davids discovered the BIND zone file parser would trip over really "
"long lines. Fix in c1624, c1625."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1409
msgid ""
"Thomas Mieslinger discovered that our webserver would only be started after "
"dropping privileges, which could cause problems. Fix in c1629."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1415
msgid ""
"Zone2sql did quite often not do exactly what was required, which users fixed "
"by editing the SQL output.  Revamped in c2032."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1421
msgid ""
"An Ubuntu user discovered in Launchpad bug 600479 that restarting database "
"threads cost a lot of memory. Normally this is rare, except in case of "
"problems. Addressed in c1676."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1427
msgid ""
"BIND backend could crash under (very) high load with very large numbers of "
"zones (hundreds of thousands).  Fixed in c1690."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1433
msgid ""
"Miek Gieben and Marco Davids spotted that PowerDNS would answer the "
"version.bind query in the IN class too.  Bug reported via twitter! Fix in "
"c1709."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1439
msgid ""
"Marcus Lauer and the OpenDNSSEC project discovered that outgoing "
"notifications did not carry the 'aa' flag.  Fixed in c1746."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1445
msgid ""
"Debugging PowerDNS, or backgrounding it, could cause crashes. Fixed by "
"Anders Kaseorg in c1747."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1450
msgid ""
"Fixed a bug that could cause crashes on launching thousands of backend "
"connections. Never observed to occur, but who knows. Fix in c1792."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1456
msgid ""
"Under some circumstances, large answers could be truncated in "
"mid-record. While technically legal, this upset a number of resolver "
"implementations (including the PowerDNS Recursor!). Fixed in c1830, "
"re-closes t200."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1463
msgid ""
"Jan Piet Mens and Florian Weimer discovered we had problems dealing with "
"escaped labels and escaped TXT fields. Fixed in c2000."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1469
msgid ""
"After 2.2 billion queries, statistics would wrap oddly. Fix in c2019, "
"closing t327."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1477
msgid ""
"Long TXT records are now split into 255-byte components "
"automatically. Implemented in c1340, reported by Darren Gamble in t188."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1483
msgid ""
"When receiving large numbers of notifications, PowerDNS would check these "
"synchronously, leading to a slowdown for other services. Fixed in c2058, "
"problem diagnosed by Richard Poole of Heart Internet."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1489
msgid ""
"Fixed compilation on newer compilers and newer versions of Boost.  Changes "
"in C1345 (closes t227), C1391, C1394, C1425, C1427, C1428, C1429, C1440, "
"C1653, thanks to Ruben Kerkhof and others."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1495
msgid "Moved Generic PostgreSQL backend over to the newer E'' style escapes. c2094."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1500
msgid "Compilation fixes for Mac OS X 10.5.7 in c1389, thanks to Tobias Markmann."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1505
msgid ""
"We can now bind to scoped IPv6 addresses, lack spotted by Darren "
"Gamble. Part of the fix is in c2018."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1510
msgid ""
"Built-in query cache can now also cache queries which lead to multiple "
"answers. Code in c2069."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1515
msgid ""
"Prodded on by Jan Piet Mens, we now support 'unknown types' (which look like "
"TYPE65534)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1520
msgid ""
"Add 'slave-renotify' to retransmit notifies for slaved zones, which is "
"helpful when acting as a 'signing slave' for a hidden master. Code in c1950."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1526
msgid "No longer let zone2sql and zone2ldap import BIND 'hint' zones. c1998."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1531
msgid ""
"Allow for timestamps to explicitly be specified in (s)econds. Code in c1398, "
"closing t250."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1536
msgid ""
"Zones with URL and MBOXFW records can be transferred over AXFR, code in "
"c1464."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1542
msgid ""
"Maik Zumstrull cleaned up the BIND Backend makefile, plus taught our init.d "
"script to read /etc/default/pdns.  Code in c1601, c1602."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1549
msgid ""
"Generic SQL backends now support multiple masters in the domains table. Code "
"in c1857. Additionally, masters can also have :port numbers. Code in c1858."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1557
msgid "Recursor version 3.3.1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1561
msgid "Unreleased"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1566
msgid ""
"Version 3.3.1 contains a small number of important fixes, adds some memory "
"usage statistics, but no new features."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1571
msgid ""
"Discovered by John J and Robin J, the PowerDNS Recursor did not process "
"packets that were truncated in mid-record, and also did not act on the "
"'truncated' (TC) flag in that case. This broke a very small number of "
"domains, most of them served by very old versions of the PowerDNS "
"Authoritative Server. Fix in c1740."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1578
msgid ""
"PowerDNS emitted a harmless, but irritating, error message on receiving "
"certain very short packets. Discovered by Winfried A and John J, fix in "
"c1729."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1584
msgid ""
"PowerDNS could crash on startup if configured to provide service on "
"malformed IPv6 addresses on FreeBSD, or in case when the FreeBSD kernel was "
"compiled without any form of IPv6 support. Debugged by Bryan Seitz, fix in "
"c1727."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1590
msgid ""
"Add max-mthread-stack metric to debug rare crashes. Could be used to save "
"memory on constrained systems. Implemented in c1745."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1595
msgid ""
"Add cache-bytes and packetcache-bytes metrics to measure our 'pre-malloc' "
"memory utilization. Implemented in c1750."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1601
msgid "Recursor version 3.3"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1605
msgid "Released on the 22nd of September 2010."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1610
msgid ""
"Version 3.3 fixes a number of small but persistent issues, rounds off our "
"IPv6 %link-level support and adds an important feature for many users of the "
"Lua scripts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1614
msgid "In addition, scalability on Solaris 10 is improved."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1621
msgid ""
"'dist-recursor' script was not compatible with pure POSIX /bin/sh, "
"discovered by Simon Kirby. Fix in c1545."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1624
msgid ""
"Simon Bedford, Brad Dameron and Laurient Papier discovered relatively high "
"TCP/IP loads could cause TCP/IP service to shut down over time.  Addressed "
"in commits C1546, C1640, C1652, C1685, C1698. Additional information "
"provided by Zwane Mwaikambo, Nicholas Miell and Jeff Roberson.  Testing by "
"Christian Hofstaedtler and Michael Renner."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1629
msgid ""
"The PowerDNS Recursor could not read the 'root zone' (this is something else "
"than the root hints) because of an unquoted TXT record.  This has now been "
"addressed, allowing operators to hardcode the root zone. This can improve "
"security if the root zone used is kept up to date.  Change in c1547."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1634
msgid ""
"A return of an old bug, when a domain gets new nameservers, but the old "
"nameservers continue to contain a copy of the domain, PowerDNS could get "
"'stuck' with the old servers.  Fixed in c1548."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1638
msgid ""
"Discovered &amp; reported by Alexander Gall of SWITCH, the Recursor used to "
"try to resolve 'AXFR' records over UDP. Fix in c1619."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1641
msgid ""
"The Recursor embedded authoritative server messed up parsing a record like "
"'@ IN MX 15 @'. Spotted by Aki Tuomi, fix in c1621."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1644
msgid ""
"The Recursor embedded authoritative server messed up parsing really really "
"long lines. Spotted by Marco Davids, fix in c1624, c1625."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1647
msgid "Packet cache was not DNS class correct. Spotted by \"Robin\", fix in c1688."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1650
msgid ""
"The packet cache would cache some NXDOMAINs for too long. Solving this bug "
"exposed an underlying oddity where the initial NXDOMAIN response had an "
"overly long (untruncated) TTL, whereas all the next ones would be ok. Solved "
"in c1679, closing t281. Especially important for RBL operators.  Fixed after "
"some nagging by Alex Broens (thanks)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1660
msgid ""
"The priming of the root now uses more IPv6 addresses. Change in c1550, "
"closes t287. Also, the IPv6 address of I.ROOT-SERVERS.NET was added in "
"c1650."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1663
msgid ""
"The <function>rec_control dump-cache</function> command now also dumps the "
"'negative query' cache. Code in c1713."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1666
msgid ""
"PowerDNS Recursor can now bind to fe80 IPv6 space with '%eth0' link "
"selection. Suggested by Darren Gamble, implemented with help from Niels "
"Bakker. Change in c1620."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1669
msgid ""
"Solaris on x86 has a long standing bug in port_getn(), which we now work "
"around. Spotted by 'Dirk' and 'AS'. Solution suggested by the Apache runtime "
"library, update in c1622."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1673
msgid ""
"New runtime statistic: 'tcp-clients' which lists the number of currently "
"active TCP/IP clients. Code in c1623."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1676
msgid ""
"Deal better with UltraDNS style CNAME redirects containing SOA "
"records. Spotted by Andy Fletcher from UKDedicated in t303, fix in c1628."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1679
msgid ""
"The packet cache, which has 'ready to use' packets containing answers, now "
"artificially ages the ready to use packets. Code in c1630."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1682
msgid ""
"Lua scripts can now indicate that certain queries will have 'variable' "
"answers, which means that the packet cache will not touch these answers.  "
"This is great for overriding some domains for some users, but not all of "
"them. Use setvariable() in Lua to indicate such domains. Code in c1636."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1686
msgid ""
"Add query statistic called 'dont-outqueries', plus add IPv6 address :: and "
"IPv4 address 0.0.0.0 to the default \"dont-query\" set, preventing the "
"Recursor from talking to itself. Code in c1637."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1690
msgid ""
"Work around a gcc 4.1 bug, still in wide use on common platforms. Code in "
"c1653."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1693
msgid ""
"Add 'ARCHFLAGS' to PowerDNS Recursor Makefile, easing 64 bit compilation on "
"mainly 32 bit platforms (and vice versa)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1696
msgid ""
"Under rare circumstances, querying the Recursor for statistics under very "
"high load could lead to a crash (although this has never been observed). Bad "
"code removed &amp; good code unified in c1675."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1700
msgid ""
"Spotted by Jeff Sipek, the rec_control manpage did not list the new get-all "
"command. c1677."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1703
msgid ""
"On some platforms, it may be better to have PowerDNS itself distribute "
"queries over threads (instead of leaving it up to the kernel).  This "
"experimental feature can be enabled with the 'pdns-distributes-queries' "
"setting. Code in c1678 and beyond. Speeds up Solaris measurably."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1707
msgid ""
"Cache cleaning code was cleaned up, unified and expanded to cover the "
"'negative cache', which used to be cleaned rather bluntly. Code in c1702, "
"further tweaks in c1712, spotted by Darren Gamble, Imre Gergely and "
"Christian Kovacic."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1713
msgid "Changes between RC1, RC2 and RC3."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1716
msgid ""
"RC2: Fixed linking on RHEL5/CentOS5, which both ship with a gcc compiler "
"that claims to support atomic operations, but doesn't. Code in "
"c1714. Spotted by 'Bas' and Imre Gergely."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1719
msgid ""
"RC2: Negative query cache was configured to grow too large, and was not "
"cleaned efficiently. Code in c1712, spotted by Imre Gergely."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1722
msgid ""
"RC3: Root failed to be renewed automatically, relied on fallback to make "
"this happen. Code in c1716, spotted by Detlef Peeters."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1728
msgid "Recursor version 3.2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1732
msgid "Released on the 7th of March 2010."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1739
msgid ""
"Lua scripts from version 3.1.7.* are fully compatible with version "
"3.2. However, scripts written for development snapshot releases, are NOT.  "
"Please see <xref linkend=\"recursor-scripting\"/> for details!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1745
msgid ""
"The 3.2 release is the first major release of the PowerDNS Recursor in a "
"long time. Partly this is because 3.1.7.* functioned very well, and "
"delivered satisfying performance, partly this is because in order to really "
"move forward, some heavy lifting had to be done."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1749
msgid ""
"As always, we are grateful for the large PowerDNS community that is actively "
"involved in improving the quality of our software, be it by submitting "
"patches, by testing development versions of our software or helping debug "
"interesting issues. We specifically want to thank Stefan Schmidt and Florian "
"Weimer, who both over the years have helped tremendously in keeping PowerDNS "
"fast, stable and secure."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1754
msgid ""
"This version of the PowerDNS Recursor contains a rather novel form of "
"lock-free multithreading, a situation that comes close to the old '--fork' "
"trick, but allows the Recursor to fully utilize multiple CPUs, while "
"delivering unified statistics and operational control."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1758
msgid ""
"In effect, this delivers the best of both worlds: near linear scaling, with "
"almost no administrative overhead."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1761
msgid ""
"Compared to 'regular multithreading', whereby threads cooperate more "
"closely, more memory is used, since each thread maintains its own DNS "
"cache.  However, given the economics, and the relatively limited total "
"amount of memory needed for high performance, this price is well worth it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1765
msgid ""
"In practical numbers, over 40,000 queries/second sustained performance has "
"now been measured by a third party, with a 100.0% packet response rate. This "
"means that the needs of around 400,000 residential connections can now be "
"met by a single commodity server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1769
msgid ""
"In addition to the above, the PowerDNS Recursor is now providing resolver "
"service for many more Internet users than ever before. This has brought with "
"it 24/7 Service Level Agreements, and 24/7 operational monitoring by "
"networking personnel at some of the largest telecommunications companies in "
"the world."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1773
msgid ""
"In order to facilitate such operation, more statistics are now provided that "
"allow the visual verification of proper PowerDNS Recursor operation. As an "
"example of this there are now graphs that plot how many queries were dropped "
"by the operating system because of a CPU overload, plus statistics that can "
"be monitored to determine if the PowerDNS deployment is under a spoofing "
"attack."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1778
msgid ""
"All in all, this is a large and important PowerDNS Release, paving the way "
"for further innovation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><note><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1783
msgid ""
"This release removes support for the 'fork' multi-processor option. In "
"addition, the default is now to spawn two threads. This has been done in "
"such a way that total memory usage will remain identical, so each thread "
"will use half of the allocated maximum number of cache entries."
