#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1790
msgid ""
"'Make install' when an existing configuration file contained a 'fork' "
"statement has been fixed. Spotted by Darren Gamble, code in c1534."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1793
msgid ""
"Reloading a non-existent allow-from-file caused the control thread to stop "
"working. Spotted by Imre Gergely, code in c1532."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1796
msgid ""
"Parser got confused by reading en empty line in auth-forward-zones. Spotted "
"by Imre Gergely, code in c1533."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1799
msgid ""
"David Gavarret discovered undocumented and not-working settings to set the "
"owner, group and access modes of the control socket. Code by Aki Tuomi and "
"documentation in c1535. Fixup in c1536 for FreeBSD as found by Ralf van der "
"Enden."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1803
msgid ""
"Tiny improvement possibly solving an issue on Solaris 10's completion port "
"event multiplexer (c1537)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1809
msgid ""
"Compilation on Solaris 10 has been fixed (various patchlevels had different "
"issues), code in c1522."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1812
msgid ""
"Compatibility with CentOS4/RHEL4 has been restored, the gcc and glibc "
"versions shipped with this distribution contain a Thread Local Storage bug "
"which we now work around. Thanks to Darren Gamble and Imre Gergely for "
"debugging this issue, code in c1527."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1816
msgid ""
"A failed setuid operation, because of misconfiguration, would result in a "
"crash instead of an error message. Fixed in c1523."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1819 docs/pdns.xml:2012
msgid ""
"Imre Gergely discovered that PowerDNS was doing spurious root repriming when "
"invalidating nssets. Fixed in c1531."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1822
msgid ""
"Imre Gergely discovered our rrd graphs had not been changed for the new "
"multithreaded world, and did not allow scaling beyond 200% cpu use. In "
"addition, CPU usage graphs did not add up correctly. Implemented in c1524."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1826
msgid ""
"Andreas Jakum discovered the description of 'max-packetcache-entries' and "
"'forward-zones-recurse' was wrong in the output of '--help' and '--config'.  "
"In addition, some stray backup files made it into the RC1 release. Addressed "
"in c1529."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1830
msgid ""
"Full release notes follow, including some overlap with the incremental "
"release notes above.  Improvements:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1835
msgid ""
"Multithreading, allowing near linear scaling to multiple CPUs or "
"cores. Configured using 'threads=' (many commits).  This also deprecates the "
"'--fork' option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1841
msgid ""
"Added ability to read a configuration item of a running PowerDNS Recursor "
"using 'rec_control get-parameter' (c1243), suggested by Wouter de Jong."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1846
msgid ""
"Added ability to read all statistics in one go of a running PowerDNS "
"Recursor using 'rec_control get-all' (c1496), suggested by Michael Renner."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1851
msgid "Speedups in packet generation (Commits C1258, C1259, C1262)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1856
msgid ""
"TCP deferred accept() filter is turned on again for slight DoS "
"protection. Code in c1414."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1861
msgid ""
"PowerDNS Recursor can now do TCP/IP queries to remote IPv6 addresses "
"(c1412)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1867
msgid ""
"Solaris 9 '/dev/poll' support added, Solaris 8 now deprecated. Changes in "
"c1421, c1422, c1424, c1413."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1873
msgid ""
"Lua functions can now also see the address _to_ which a question was sent, "
"using getlocaladdress(). Implemented in c1309 and c1315."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1878
msgid ""
"Maximum cache sizes now default to a sensible value. Suggested by Roel van "
"der Made, implemented in c1354."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1883
msgid ""
"Domains can now be forwarded to IPv6 addresses too, using either ::1 syntax "
"or [::1]:25. Thanks to Wijnand Modderman for discovering this issue, fixed "
"in c1349."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1888
msgid ""
"Lua scripts can now load libraries at runtime, for example to calculate md5 "
"hashes. Code by Winfried Angele in c1405."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1894
msgid ""
"Periodic statistics output now includes average queries per second, as well "
"as packet cache numbers (c1493)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1899
msgid ""
"New metrics are available for graphing, plus added to the default graphs "
"(c1495, c1498, c1503)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1905
msgid ""
"Fix errors/crashes on more recent versions of Solaris 10, where the ports "
"functions could return ENOENT under some circumstances. Reported and "
"debugged by Jan Gyselinck, fixed in c1372."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1914
msgid ""
"Add pdnslog() function for Lua scripts, so errors or other messages can be "
"logged properly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1918
msgid ""
"New settings to set the owner, group and access modes of the control socket "
"(socket-owner, socket-group, socket-mode). Code by Aki Tuomi and "
"documentation in c1535. Fixup in c1536 for FreeBSD as found by Ralf van der "
"Enden."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1923
msgid ""
"rec_control now accepts a --timeout parameter, which can be useful when "
"reloading huge Lua scripts. Implemented in c1366."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1928
msgid ""
"Domains can now be forwarded with the 'recursion-desired' bit on or off, "
"using either <command>forward-zones-recurse</command> or by prefixing the "
"name of a zone with a '+' in <command>forward-zones-file</command>. Feature "
"suggested by Darren Gamble, implemented in c1451."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1934
msgid "Access control lists can now be reloaded at runtime (implemented in c1457)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1939
msgid ""
"PowerDNS Recursor can now use a pool of query-local-addresses to further "
"increase resilience against spoofing. Suggested by Ad Spelt, implemented in "
"c1426."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1944
msgid ""
"PowerDNS Recursor now also has a packet cache, greatly speeding up "
"operations. Implemented in c1426, c1433 and further."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1949
msgid ""
"Cache can be limited in how long it maximally stores records, for BIND "
"compatibility (TTL limiting), by setting "
"<command>max-cache-ttl</command>.Idea by Winfried Angele, implemented in "
"c1438."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1954
msgid ""
"Cache cleaning turned out to be scanning more of the cache than necessary "
"for cache maintenance. In addition, far more frequent but smaller cache "
"cleanups improve responsiveness. Thanks to Winfried Angele for discovering "
"this issue. (commits C1501, C1507)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1961
msgid ""
"Performance graphs enhanced with separate CPU load and cache effectiveness "
"plots, plus display of various overload situations (commits C1503)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1967
msgid "Compiler/Operating system/Library updates:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1971
msgid ""
"PowerDNS Recursor can now compile against newer versions of Boost (verified "
"up to and including 1.42.0). Reported &amp; fixed by Darix in c1274. Further "
"fixes in c1275, c1276, c1277, c1283."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1976
msgid ""
"Fix compatibility with newer versions of GCC (closes ticket t227, spotted by "
"Ruben Kerkhof, code in c1345, more fixes in commit C1394, C1416, C1440)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1981
msgid ""
"Rrdtool update graph is now compatible with FreeBSD out of the box. Thanks "
"to Bryan Seitz (c1517)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1986
msgid "Fix up Makefile for older versions of Make (c1229)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1991
msgid "Solaris compilation improvements (out of the box, no handwork needed)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:1996
msgid ""
"Solaris 9 MTasker compilation fixes, as suggested by John Levon. Changes in "
"c1431."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2006
msgid ""
"Under rare circumstances, the recursor could crash on 64 bit Linux systems "
"running glibc 2.7, as found in Debian Lenny.  These circumstances became a "
"lot less rare for the 3.2 release. Discovered by Andreas Jakum and debugged "
"by #powerdns, fix in c1519."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2016
msgid ""
"Configuration parser is now resistant against trailing tabs and other "
"whitespace (c1242)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2022
msgid ""
"Fix typo in a Lua error message. Close t210, as reported by Stefan Schmidt "
"(c1319)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2027
msgid ""
"Profiled-build instructions were broken, discovered &amp; fixes suggested by "
"Stefan Schmidt. t239, fix in c1462."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2032
msgid ""
"Fix up duplicate SOA from a remote authoritative server from showing up in "
"our output (c1475)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2038
msgid "All security fixes from 3.1.7.2 are included."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2044
msgid ""
"Under highly exceptional circumstances on FreeBSD the PowerDNS Recursor "
"could crash because of a TCP/IP error.  Reported and fixed by Andrei Poelov "
"in t192, fixed in c1280."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2050
msgid ""
"PowerDNS Recursor can be a root-server again. Error spotted by the ever "
"vigilant Darren Gamble (t229), fix in c1458."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2056
msgid ""
"Rare TCP/IP errors no longer lead to PowerDNS Recursor logging errors or "
"becoming confused. Debugged by Josh Berry of Plusnet PLC. Code in c1457."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2062
msgid ""
"Do not hammer parent servers in case child zones are misconfigured, requery "
"at most once every 10 seconds. Reported &amp; investigated by Stefan Schmidt "
"and Andreas Jakum, fixed in c1265."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2068
msgid ""
"Properly process answers from remote authoritative servers that send error "
"answers without including the original question (c1329, c1327)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2074
msgid ""
"No longer spontaneously turn on 'export-etc-hosts' after reloading "
"zones. Discovered by Paul Cairney, reported in t225, addressed in c1348."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2080
msgid ""
"Very abrupt server failure of large numbers of high-volume authoritative "
"servers could trigger an out of memory situation. Addressed in c1505."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2087
msgid ""
"Make timeouts for queries to remote authoritative servers configurable with "
"millisecond granularity. In addition, the old code turned out to consider "
"the timeout expired when the integral number of seconds since 1970 increased "
"by 1 - which *on average* is after 500ms. This might have caused spurious "
"timeouts! New default timeout is 1500ms. See "
"<command>network-timeout</command> setting for more details.  Code in c1402."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2098
msgid "Recursor version 3.1.7.2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2102
msgid "Released on the 6th of January 2010."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2107
msgid ""
"This release consist of a number of vital security updates. These updates "
"address issues that can in all likelihood lead to a full system "
"compromise. In addition, it is possible for third parties to pollute your "
"cache with dangerous data, exposing your users to possible harm."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2112
msgid ""
"This version has been well tested, and at the time of this release is "
"already powering millions of internet connections, and should therefore be a "
"risk-free upgrade from 3.1.7.1 or any earlier version of the PowerDNS "
"Recursor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2117
msgid ""
"All known versions of the PowerDNS Recursor are impacted to a greater or "
"lesser extent, so an immediate update is advised."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2120
msgid ""
"These vulnerabilities were discovered by a third party that can't yet be "
"named, but who we thank for their contribution to a more secure PowerDNS "
"Recursor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2124
msgid ""
"For more information, see <xref linkend=\"powerdns-advisory-2010-01\"/> and "
"<xref linkend=\"powerdns-advisory-2010-02\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2128
msgid "Recursor version 3.1.7.1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2132
msgid "Released on the 2nd of August 2009."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2137
msgid ""
"This release consists entirely of fixes for tiny bugs that have been "
"reported over the past year. In addition, compatibility has been restored "
"with the latest versions of the gcc compiler and the 'boost' libraries."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2141
msgid ""
"No features have been added, but some debugging code that very slightly "
"impacted performance (and polluted the console when operating in the "
"foreground) has been removed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2145
msgid ""
"FreeBSD users may want to upgrade because of a very remote chance of 3.1.7 "
"and previous crashing once every few years.  For other operators not "
"currently experiencing problems, there is no reason to upgrade."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2152
msgid ""
"Improved error messages when parsing zones for authoritative serving "
"(c1235)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2158
msgid ""
"Better resilience against whitespace in configuration (changesets C1237, "
"C1240, C1242)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2164
msgid "Slight performance increase (c1378)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2170
msgid ""
"Fix rare case where timeouts were not being reported to the right "
"query-thread (c1260)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2176
msgid "Fix compilation against newer versions of the Boost C++ libraries (c1381)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2182
msgid ""
"Close very rare issue with TCP/IP close reporting ECONNRESET on "
"FreeBSD. Reported by Andrei Poelov in t192."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2187
msgid "Silence debugging output (c1286)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2192
msgid "Fix compilation against newer versions of gcc (c1384)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2197
msgid ""
"No longer set export-etc-hosts to 'on' on reload-zones. Discovered by Paul "
"Cairney, closes t225."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2202
msgid ""
"Sane default for the maximum cache size in the Recursor, suggested by Roel "
"van der Made (c1354)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2208
msgid ""
"No longer exit because of the changed behaviour of the Solaris 'completion "
"ports' in more recent versions of Solaris. Fix in c1372, reported by Jan "
"Gyselinck."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2215
msgid "Authoritative Server version 2.9.22"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2219
msgid "Released on the 27th of January 2009."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2224
msgid ""
"This is a huge release, spanning almost 20 months of development. Besides "
"fixing a lot of bugs, of note is the addition of the so called 'Notification "
"Proxy', which allows PowerDNS to function as a master server behind a "
"firewall, plus the huge performance improvement of the internal caches."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2228
msgid "This work has been made possible by UPC Broadband and Directi, respectively."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2231
msgid ""
"Finally, the release candidates of this version have been tested &amp; "
"improved by Jorn Ekkelenkamp, Ton van Rosmalen, Jeff Sipek, Tyler Hall, "
"Christof Meerwald and Stefan Schmidt."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2235
msgid "Fixed between rc1 and rc2, but not an issue in 2.9.21."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2239
msgid ""
"<command>pdns_control ccounts</command> again outputs proper cache "
"statistics. Implemented in c1304."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2244
msgid ""
"Negative query caching was reinstated, leading to 6 times fewer backend "
"queries than rc1 on the Express.powerdns.com servers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2249
msgid ""
"Packetcache no longer needlessly parses outgoing packets before sending "
"them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2254
msgid ""
"Fancy records work again. This work has been sponsored by ISP "
"Services. Implemented in c1302 and c1299."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2265
msgid ""
"<command>pdns_control</command> can now also work over TCP/IP. Sponsored by "
"Directi. Commits C1246, C1251, C1254, C1255."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2270
msgid ""
"Implemented a notification proxy, see <xref linkend=\"nproxy\"/>. This work "
"was sponsored by UPC Broadband. Implemented in commits C1075, C1077, C1082, "
"C1083, C1085 and C1086."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2276
msgid ""
"IXFR queries are now supported in the sense that we treat them as AXFR "
"queries, silencing warnings in other nameservers. Suggested in t131."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2281
msgid ""
"The PIPE backend has been extended by David Apgar to allow the reporting of "
"errors using the 'FAIL' command, plus support for responses with "
"whitespace. Implemented in c1114."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2287
msgid ""
"PowerDNS Authoritative server now parses incoming EDNS options, like maximum "
"allowed packet size. Implemented in c1123 and c1281."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2292
msgid ""
"Added support for DHCID, IPSECKEY and KX records, thanks Norbert Sendetzky "
"for the hint. Implemented in c1144."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2298
msgid ""
"Norbert Sendetzky has has added support for all record types supported by "
"PowerDNS to the LDAPBackend. Furthermore, the detection of OpenLDAP in "
"autoconf has been improved. Finally, debian has supplied some fixes to "
"PowerLDAP. Implemented in c1152 and c1153."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2304
msgid ""
"Implemented EDNS NSID option for retrieving the nameserver ID out of "
"band. Defaults to hostname, can be specified using the "
"<command>server-id</command> setting. Code in c1232."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2310
msgid ""
"Implemented experimental EDNS PING for enhanced forgery resilience. Code in "
"c1232."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2316 docs/pdns.xml:2854 docs/pdns.xml:6553
msgid "Performance:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2320
msgid ""
"Improve packet generation performance, in some cases by 25%. Code in C1258, "
"C1259."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2325
msgid "Improved access list checking performance. c1261."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2330
msgid ""
"PowerDNS Authoritative caches were completely redone, and are now based on "
"the same cache that is in the resolver. This work has been sponsored by "
"Directi. In large benchmarks, PowerDNS performance has improved by an order "
"of magnitude or more. This new version allows for near-instantaneous cache "
"purging, plus very rapid purging based on suffix. Purge commands can also be "
"batched. This work is partially based on an innovative reverse-string "
"comparison function authored by Aki Tuomi."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2338
msgid ""
"Installations which run with very high cache hitrates can now benefit from "
"multiple CPUs by setting <command>receiver-threads</command> to the number "
"of desired CPUs to utilize in cache operations. Implemented in c1316."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2344
msgid ""
"BIND backend speedups in c1108, measured at around a 20% improvement, "
"possibly more on very large setups."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2355
msgid ""
"Tyler Hall discovered the PowerDNS configuration file parser had problems "
"with trailing tabs. This turned out to be a wider problem in PowerDNS.  "
"Buggy code replaced by a library call in c1237 and c1240."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2361
msgid ""
"David Apgar of Yahoo discovered that our 'guardian' method of restarting "
"PowerDNS in case of problems was not fool proof, and submitted a fix.  A "
"variation of this fix can be found in c1323. Also reported by Directi."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2368
msgid ""
"Connection reset by peer events in the TCP nameserver no longer lead to the "
"cycling of database connections. Code in c1241."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2373
msgid ""
"FreeBSD compilation with Generic PostgreSQL backend was fixed. Reported by "
"Wouter de Jong of WideXS, fixed in c1305, closes t95."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2379
msgid ""
"Webserver no longer prints '1e2%'. Finally closes t26. Much friendly nagging "
"for over 3 years by Jeff Sipek, code in c1303."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2384
msgid ""
"PowerDNS used to ignore certain queries it could not answer. These queries "
"are no longer ignored, but get a SERVFAIL response. Implemented in c1239."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2390
msgid ""
"Fix subtle CNAME and wildcard interactions reported by 'zzyzz', implemented "
"in c1147."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2395
msgid ""
"The generic backends did not honour the <command>default-ttl</command> "
"setting. Spotted and implemented by Matti Hiljanen."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2400
msgid ""
"Matti Hiljanen discovered that the OpenDBX backend did not fill out the SOA "
"ttl value properly. Matti also improved the SQL statements for better "
"compatibility. Implemented in c1181."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2407
msgid ""
"Treat invalid WWW requests better. Spotted by Maikel Verheijen, implemented "
"in c1092."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2412
msgid ""
"Documentation errors and typos, spotted by Marco Davids (c1097) and Rejo "
"Zengers (c1119)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2417
msgid ""
"Properly fill out the 'recursion available'-flag. Spotted by Augie Schwer in "
"t167."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2422
msgid ""
"Several memory leaks on bad data in the database or other errors have been "
"fixed. Addressed in C1078 and C1079."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2427
msgid ""
"In contravention to the documentation, the domain type as specified in the "
"database ('MASTER', 'SLAVE' or 'NATIVE') was interpreted case "
"sensitively. C1084."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2433
msgid ""
"BIND backend could crash on processing information about slave zones to be "
"checked. Spotted by Stefan Schmidt, fixed in C1089."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2439
msgid ""
"Jelte Jansen of Stichting NLNetLabs discovered PowerDNS in BIND mode "
"couldn't operate as a root-server! Fixed in C1057."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2444
msgid ""
"'DPS' discovered there was a rare opportunity for PowerDNS to lock up "
"waiting for new data. Addressed in C1076."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2450
msgid "Make singlethreaded mode more resilient against errors. c1272."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2455
msgid ""
"DNSSEC records were part of 2.9.21, but were not actually hooked up. Please "
"note that while PowerDNS can serve most DNSSEC records, it does not do "
"DNSSEC processing. Implemented in C1046."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2461
msgid ""
"Shawn Starr migrated all his domains to PowerDNS in one evening, from an "
"installation that had been used since BIND4.  In doing so, he found 3 bugs "
"in as many hours. An <command>IN</command> statement in the BIND "
"<filename>named.conf</filename> with a zone with a trailing dot was "
"misparsed, fixed in c1233. Secondly, the zone file parser tripped over a "
"line consisting of nothing but comments in the wrong place. Finally '$ORIGIN "
".' was misparsed. Last two issues fixed in c1234."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2470
msgid ""
"Our statistics counters did not wrap correctly after the 2.15 billion "
"mark. Spotted by Stefan Schmidt, reported in t179, fixed in c1284."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2475
msgid ""
"Bindbackend could sometimes generate very strange error messages while "
"processing a malformed zone file. Sometimes such error messages could cause "
"a crash (reported on HP-UX). Addressed by c1279. This could not be triggered "
"remotely. Closes ticket t203."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2481
msgid ""
"Pipe backend did not clean up killed coprocesses. Found and fixed by Daniel "
"Drown"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2486
msgid ""
"Installations with tens of thousands of slave domains would never complete "
"the cycle to check the freshness of all zones as each incoming notification "
"disrupted this cycle. Addressed in cooperation with Tyler Hall of EditDNS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2498
msgid ""
"Zone parser improvements mean $TTL and $INCLUDES now work a lot "
"better. Implemented in C1056, C1062."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2503
msgid ""
"No longer report temporary recvfrom errors, which used to spam the log on "
"many systems. Addressed in c1320."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2509
msgid ""
"Direct queries for 'fancy records' would lead to errors, such queries now "
"fail early. Spotted by Jorn Ekkelenkamp, implemented in C1051."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2514
msgid "Fix typo in geobackend, closing t157, implemented in C1090."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2519
msgid "Initial work on TSIG support - not done yet. Spurred on by Marco Davids."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2524
msgid ""
"Embarrassingly, the 'master' configuration setting was not documented in the "
"list of all settings!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2529
msgid ""
"Norbert has updated OpenDBX so that SQLite reads and writes no longer "
"deadlock, plus compilation fixes on Solaris, plus the addition of "
"autoserials to backends that support triggers. Implemented in c1154."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2535
msgid ""
"Random generator is now based on AES, improving the security of certain "
"proxy operations. This is the same random generator that is in the "
"recursor. Implemented in c1256."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2541
msgid "Documentation for 'supermaster' mode was improved due to popular demand."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2547 docs/pdns.xml:2619
msgid ""
"When binding to a UDP port failed, supply a more precise error message "
"(c1245)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2553
msgid ""
"The zone parser error messages were vastly improved, partially inspired by "
"Shawn's cowboy migration. Code in c1235."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2558
msgid ""
"Labels are compressed more efficiently (case-insensitively), leading to "
"smaller packets. Implemented in c1156."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2564
msgid ""
"Fix handling of TCP timeouts to not cause a reload of the "
"backends. Implemented in c1092."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2569
msgid ""
"TCP Receiver no longer spams the log with common network errors. Implemented "
"in c1306."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2575
msgid ""
"Move from select() to poll()-based multiplexing, allowing PowerDNS to listen "
"on more than 1024 sockets simultaneously.  One big PowerDNS user needs "
"this. Implemented in C1072."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2581
msgid ""
"Zone2sql now reads source files in performance enhancing inode "
"order. Additionally, zone2sql no longer dies on a missing zone file if "
"<command>--on-error-resume-next</command> was specified. Finally, statistics "
"of zone2sql conversion have been improved. Implemented in C1055."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2588
msgid ""
"Address issues found by more recent g++ versions. Spotted and/or fixed by "
"Jorn Ekkelenkamp (c1051), Marcus Rueckert (c1094), Norbert Sendetzky "
"(c1107), Serge Belyshev (c1171)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2594
msgid ""
"The Intel C Compiler implements certain things differently, causing the "
"master/slave communicator to malfunction. Spotted by Marcus Rueckert, "
"implemented in C1052, plus fallout in C1105."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2600
msgid "PowerDNS can now be compiled with Boost 1.37.0."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2605
msgid ""
"Andre Lorbach of Adiscon discovered the Microsoft Windows 2003 nameserver "
"adds out of zone data to zone transfers, which we need to ignore, instead of "
"rejecting the entire zone. Implemented in C1048."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2612
msgid ""
"PowerDNS now skips remote master servers which consistently generate timeout "
"messages, improving the master checking cycle time tremendously.  Developed "
"in cooperation with Tyler Hall. Implemented in c1278."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2624
msgid ""
"<command>dnsreplay</command> now waits for the final answers to arrive, "
"making it possible to process even small pcap files and get meaningful "
"statistics. c1268."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2630
msgid ""
"<command>dnsreplay</command> has a more sane default timeout now, which can "
"be configured too. Suggested by Augie Schwer in t163, implemented in c1287."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2636
msgid "Authoritative Server version 2.9.21.2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2638
msgid "Released on the 18th of November 2008."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2641
msgid ""
"This release consists of a single patch to PowerDNS Authoritative Server "
"version 2.9.21.1.  In some configurations, notably with configuration option "
"'distributor-threads=1', the PowerDNS Authoritative Server crashes easily in "
"some error conditions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2646
msgid ""
"All users are urged to upgrade. Even though PowerDNS restarts itself on "
"encountering such error conditions, and even though most PowerDNS "
"configurations do not run in single threaded mode, an upgrade is "
"recommended."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2650
msgid "More detail can be found in <xref linkend=\"powerdns-advisory-2008-03\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2653
msgid "Authoritative Server version 2.9.21.1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2655
msgid "Released on the 6th of August 2008."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2658
msgid ""
"This release consists of a single patch to PowerDNS Authoritative Server "
"version 2.9.21.  Brian J. Dowling of Simplicity Communications has "
"discovered a security implication of the previous PowerDNS behaviour to drop "
"queries it considers malformed. We are grateful that Brian notified us "
"quickly about this problem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2664
msgid ""
"This issue has been assigned CVE-2008-3337. The single patch is in "
"c1239. More detail can be found in <xref "
"linkend=\"powerdns-advisory-2008-02\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2668 docs/pdns.xml:8881
msgid ""
"The implication is that while the PowerDNS Authoritative server itself does "
"not face a security risk because of dropping these malformed queries, other "
"resolving nameservers run a higher risk of accepting spoofed answers for "
"domains being hosted by PowerDNS Authoritative Servers before 2.9.21.1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2673 docs/pdns.xml:8886
msgid ""
"While the dropping of queries does not aid sophisticated spoofing attempts, "
"it does facilitate simpler attacks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2676
msgid ""
"It may be good to know that several large sites already run with this patch "
"applied, as it has been in the public code base for some weeks already."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2680
msgid "Recursor version 3.1.7"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2682
msgid "Released the 25th of June 2008."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2685
msgid ""
"This version contains powerful scripting abilities, allowing operators to "
"modify DNS responses in many interesting ways. Among other things, these "
"abilities can be used to filter out malware domains, to perform load "
"balancing, to comply with legal and other requirements and finally, to "
"implement 'NXDOMAIN' redirection."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2690
msgid ""
"It is hoped that the addition of Lua scripting will enable responsible DNS "
"modification for those that need it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2693
msgid ""
"For more details about the Lua scripting, which can be modified, loaded and "
"unloaded at runtime, see <xref linkend=\"recursor-scripting\"/>.  Many "
"thanks are due to the #lua irc channel, for excellent near-realtime Lua "
"support. In addition, a number of PowerDNS users have been enthousiastically "
"testing prereleases of the scripting support, and have found and solved many "
"issues."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2698
msgid "In addition, 3.1.7 fixes a number of bugs:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2705
msgid ""
"In 3.1.5 and 3.1.6, an authoritative server could continue to renew its "
"authority, even though a domain had been delegated to other servers in the "
"meantime."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2709
msgid ""
"In the rare cases where this happened, and the old servers were not shut "
"down, the observed effect is that users were fed outdated data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2712
msgid "Bug spotted and analysed by Darren Gamble, fix in c1182 and c1183."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2717
msgid ""
"Thanks to long time PowerDNS contributor Stefan Arentz, for the first time, "
"Mac OS X 10.5 users can compile and run the PowerDNS Recursor! Patch in "
"c1185."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2723
msgid ""
"Sten Spans spotted that for outgoing TCP/IP queries, the "
"<command>query-local-address</command> setting was not honored. Fixed in "
"c1190."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2728
msgid ""
"<command>rec_control wipe-cache</command> now also wipes domains from the "
"negative cache, hurrying up the expiry of negatively cached "
"records. Suggested by Simon Kirby, implemented in c1204."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2734
msgid ""
"When a forwarder server is configured for a domain, using the "
"<command>forward-zones</command> setting, this server IP address was "
"filtered using the <command>dont-query</command> setting, which is generally "
"not what is desired: the server to which queries are forwarded will often "
"live in private IP space, and the operator should be trusted to know what he "
"is doing. Reported and argued by Simon Kirby, fix in c1211."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2743
msgid ""
"Marcus Rueckert of OpenSUSE reported that very recent gcc versions emitted a "
"(correct) warning on an overly complicated line in syncres.cc, fixed in "
"c1189."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2749
msgid ""
"Stefan Schmidt discovered that the netmask matching code, used by the new "
"Lua scripts, but also by all other parts of PowerDNS, had problems with "
"explicit '/32' matches. Fixed in c1205."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2758
msgid "Recursor version 3.1.6"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2760
msgid "Released on the 1st of May 2008."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2763
msgid ""
"This version fixes two important problems, each on its own important enough "
"to justify a quick upgrade."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2768
msgid ""
"Version 3.1.5 had problems resolving several slightly misconfigured domains, "
"including for a time 'juniper.net'. Nameserver timeouts were not being "
"processed correctly, leading PowerDNS to not update the internal clock, "
"which in turn meant that any queries immediately following an error would "
"time out as well. Because of retries, this would usually not be a problem "
"except on very busy servers, for domains with different nameservers at "
"different levels of the DNS-hierarchy, like 'juniper.net'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2774
msgid ""
"This issue was fixed rapidly because of the help of <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.xs4all.nl\">XS4ALL</ulink> (Eric Veldhuyzen, Kai Storbeck), "
"Brad Dameron and Kees Monshouwer. Fix in c1178."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2780
msgid ""
"The new high-quality random generator was not used for all random numbers, "
"especially in source port selection. This means that 3.1.5 is still a lot "
"more secure than 3.1.4 was, and its algorithms more secure than most other "
"nameservers, but it also means 3.1.5 is not as secure as it could be.  A "
"quick upgrade is recommended. Discovered by Thomas Biege of Novell (SUSE), "
"fixed in c1179."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2787
msgid "Recursor version 3.1.5"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2789
msgid "Released on the 31st of March 2008."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2792
msgid ""
"Much like 3.1.4, this release does not add a lot of major features. Instead, "
"performance has been improved significantly (estimated at around 20%), and "
"many rare and not so rare issues were addressed. Multi-part TXT records now "
"work as expected - the only significant functional bug found in 15 "
"months. One of the oldest feature requests was fulfilled: version 3.1.5 can "
"finally forward queries for designated domains to multiple servers, on "
"differing port numbers if needed.  Previously only one forwarder address was "
"supported. This lack held back a number of migrations to PowerDNS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2798 docs/pdns.xml:8752
msgid ""
"We would like to thank Amit Klein of Trusteer for bringing a serious "
"vulnerability to our attention which would enable a smart attacker to "
"'spoof' previous versions of the PowerDNS Recursor into accepting possibly "
"malicious data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2804
msgid ""
"Details can be found on <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.trusteer.com/docs/powerdnsrecursor.html\">this Trusteer "
"page</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2807 docs/pdns.xml:8765
msgid ""
"It is recommended that all users of the PowerDNS Recursor upgrade to 3.1.5 "
"as soon as practicable, while we simultaneously note that busy servers are "
"less susceptible to the attack, but not immune."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2812
msgid ""
"The PowerDNS Security Advisory can be found in <xref "
"linkend=\"powerdns-advisory-2008-01\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2815
msgid ""
"This version can properly benefit from all IPv4 and IPv6 addresses in use at "
"the root-servers as of early February 2008. In order to implement this, "
"changes were made to how the Recursor deals internally with A and AAAA "
"queries for nameservers, see below for more details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2819
msgid ""
"Additionally, newer releases of the G++ compiler required some fixes (see "
"t173)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2822
msgid ""
"This release was made possible by the help of Wichert Akkerman, Winfried "
"Angele, Arnoud Bakker (Fox-IT), Niels Bakker (no relation!), Leo Baltus "
"(Nederlandse Publieke Omroep), Marco Davids (SIDN), David Gavarret (Neuf "
"Cegetel), Peter Gervai, Marcus Goller (UPC), Matti Hiljanen "
"(Saunalahti/Elisa), Ruben Kerkhof, Alex Kiernan, Amit Klein (Trusteer), "
"Kenneth Marshall (Rice University), Thomas Rietz, Marcus Rueckert "
"(OpenSUSE), Augie Schwer (Sonix), Sten Spans (Bit), Stefan Schmidt "
"(Freenet), Kai Storbeck (xs4all), Alex Trull, Andrew Turnbull (No Wires) and "
"Aaron Thompson, and many more who filed bugs anonymously, or who we forgot "
"to mention."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2830
msgid "Security related issues:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2834
msgid ""
"Amit Klein has informed us that System random generator output can be "
"predicted based on its past behaviour, allowing a smart attacker to 'spoof' "
"our nameserver. Full details in <xref "
"linkend=\"powerdns-advisory-2008-01\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2840
msgid ""
"The Recursor will by default no longer query private-space nameservers. This "
"closes a slight security risk and simultaneously improves performance and "
"stability. For more information, see <command>dont-query</command> in <xref "
"linkend=\"recursor-settings\"/>.  Implemented in c923."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2847
msgid ""
"Applied fix for t110 ('PowerDNS should change directory to '/' in chroot), "
"implemented in c944."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2858
msgid ""
"The DNS packet writing and parsing infrastructure performance was improved "
"in several ways, see commits C925, C926, C928, C931, C1021, C1050."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2864
msgid "Remove multithreading overhead from the Recursor (c999)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2874
msgid ""
"Built-in authoritative server now properly derives the TTL from the SOA "
"record if not specified. Implemented in c1165.  Additionally, even when TTL "
"was specified for the built-in authoritative server, it was "
"ignored. Reported by Stefan Schmidt, closing t147."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2881
msgid ""
"Empty TXT record components can now be served. Implemented in c1166, closing "
"t178. Spotted by Matti Hiljanen."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2886
msgid ""
"The Recursor would not properly override old data with new, sometimes "
"serving old and new data concurrently. Fixed in c1137."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2891
msgid ""
"SOA records with embedded carriage-return characters are now parsed "
"correctly. Implemented in c1167, closing t162."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2896
msgid ""
"Some routing conditions could cause UDP connected sockets to generate an "
"error which PowerDNS did not deal with properly, leading to a leaked file "
"descriptor. As these run out over time, the recursor could crash. This would "
"also happen for IPv6 queries on a host with no IPv6 connectivity. Thanks to "
"Kai of xs4all and Wichert Akkerman for reporting this issue. Fix in c1133."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2904
msgid ""
"Empty unknown record types can now be stored without generating a scary "
"error (c1129)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2909
msgid ""
"Applied fix for t111, t112 and t153 - large (multipart) TXT records are now "
"retrieved and served properly. Fix in c996."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2916
msgid ""
"Solaris compilation instructions in Recursor documentation were wrong, "
"leading to an instant crash on startup.  Luckily nobody reads the "
"documentation, except for Marcus Goller who found the error. Fixed in c1124."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2922
msgid ""
"On Solaris, finally fix the issue where queries get distributed strangely "
"over CPUs, or not get distributed at all.  Much debugging and analysing "
"performed by Alex Kiernan, who also supplied fixes. Implemented in c1091, "
"c1093."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2928
msgid ""
"Various fixes for modern G++ versions, most spotted by Marcus Rueckert "
"(commits C964, C965, C1028, C1052), and Ruben Kerkhof (c1136, closing t175)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2934
msgid ""
"Recursor would not properly clean up pidfile and control socket, closing "
"t120, code in c988, c1098 (part of fix by Matti Hiljanen, spotted by Leo "
"Baltus)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2939
msgid ""
"Recursor can now serve multi-line records from its limited authoritative "
"server (c1014)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2944
msgid ""
"When parsing zones, the 'm' time specification stands for minutes, not "
"months! Closing Debian bug 406462 (c1026)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2949
msgid ""
"Authoritative zone parser did not support '@' in the content of "
"records. Spotted by Marco Davids, fixed in c1030."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2954
msgid ""
"Authoritative zone parser could be confused by trailing TABs on record lines "
"(c1062)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2960
msgid ""
"EINTR error code could block entire server if received at the wrong "
"time. Spotted by Arnoud Bakker, fix in c1059."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2965
msgid ""
"Fix crash on NetBSD on Alpha CPUs, might improve startup behaviour on empty "
"caches on other architectures as well (c1061)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2970
msgid ""
"Outbound TCP queries were being performed sub-optimally because of an "
"interaction with the 'MPlexer'. Fixes in c1115, c1116."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2980
msgid ""
"Implemented <command>rec_control</command> command <command>get "
"uptime</command>, as suggested by Niels Bakker (c935). Added to default "
"rrdtool scripts in c940."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2986
msgid ""
"The Recursor Authoritative component, meant for having the Recursor serve "
"some zones authoritatively, now supports $INCLUDE and $GENERATE. Implemented "
"in c951 and c952, c967 (discovered by Thomas Rietz),"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2992
msgid ""
"Implemented <command>forward-zones-file</command> option in order to support "
"larger amounts of zones which should be forwarded to another nameserver "
"(c963)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:2998
msgid ""
"Both <command>forward-zones</command> and "
"<command>forward-zones-file</command> can now specify multiple forwarders "
"per domain, implemented in c1168, closing t81. Additionally, both these "
"settings can also specify non-standard port numbers, as suggested in ticket "
"t122. Patch authored by Aaron Thompson, with additional work by Augie "
"Schwer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3005
msgid ""
"Sten Spans contributed <command>allow-from-file</command>, implemented in "
"c1150. This feature allows the Recursor to read access rules from a (large) "
"file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3012
msgid "General improvements:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3016
msgid ""
"Ruben Kerkhof fixed up weird permission bits as well as our SGML "
"documentation code in c936 and c937."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3021
msgid ""
"Full IPv6 parity. If configured to use IPv6 for outgoing queries (using "
"<command>query-local-address6=::0</command> for example), IPv6 and IPv4 "
"addresses are finally treated 100% identically, instead of 'mostly'. This "
"feature is implemented using 'ANY' queries to find A and AAAA addresses in "
"one query, which is a new approach. Treat with caution."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3028
msgid ""
"Now perform EDNS0 root refreshing queries, so as to benefit from all "
"returned addresses. Relevant since early February 2008 when the root-servers "
"started to respond with IPv6 addresses, which made the default non-EDNS0 "
"maximum packet length reply no longer contain all records. Implemented in "
"c1130.  Thanks to dns-operations AT mail.oarc.isc.org for quick suggestions "
"on how to deal with this change."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3035
msgid ""
"<command>rec_control</command> now has a timeout in case the Recursor does "
"not respond. Implemented in c945."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3040
msgid "(Error) messages are now logged with saner priorities (c955)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3045
msgid ""
"Outbound query IP interface stemmed from 1997 (!) and was in dire need of a "
"cleanup (c1117)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3050
msgid "L.ROOT-SERVERS.NET moved (c1118)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3056
msgid "PowerDNS Authoritative Server version 2.9.21"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3058
msgid "Released the 21st of April 2007."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3061
msgid ""
"This is the first release the PowerDNS Authoritative Server since the "
"Recursor was split off to a separate product, and also marks the transfer of "
"the new technology developed specifically for the recursor, back to the "
"authoritative server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3065
msgid ""
"This move has reduced the amount of code of the Authoritative server by over "
"2000 lines, while improving the quality of the program enormously."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3069
msgid ""
"However, since so much has been changed, care should be taken when deploying "
"2.9.21."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3072
msgid ""
"To signify the magnitude of the underlying improvements, the next release of "
"the PowerDNS Authoritative Server will be called 3.0."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3075
msgid ""
"This release would not have been possible without large amounts of help and "
"support from the PowerDNS Community. We specifically want to thank Massimo "
