msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3085 docs/pdns.xml:3394 docs/pdns.xml:4685
msgid "Security issues:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3089
msgid ""
"The previous packet parsing and generating code contained no known bugs, but "
"was however very lengthy and overly complex, and might have had security "
"problems. The new code is 'inherently safe' because it relies on "
"bounds-checking C++ constructs. Therefore, a move to 2.9.21 is highly "
"recommended."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3096
msgid ""
"Pre-2.9.21, communication between master and server nameservers was not "
"checked as rigidly as possible, possibly allowing third parties to disrupt "
"but not modify such communications."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3105
msgid ""
"The 'bind1' legacy version of our BIND backend has been dropped! There "
"should be no need to rely on this old version anymore, as the main BIND "
"backend has been very well tested recently."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3111 docs/pdns.xml:3412 docs/pdns.xml:5228 docs/pdns.xml:6477
msgid "Bugs:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3115
msgid ""
"Multi-part TXT records weren't supported. This has been fixed, and "
"regression tests have been added. Code in commits C1016, C996, C994."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3120
msgid ""
"Email addresses with embedded dots in SOA records were not parsed correctly, "
"nor were other embedded dots. Noted by 'Bastiaan', fixed in c1026."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3125
msgid ""
"BIND backend treated the 'm' TTL modifier as 'months' and not "
"'minutes'. Closes Debian bug 406462. Addressed in c1026."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3130
msgid ""
"Our snapshots were built against a static version of PostgreSQL that was "
"incompatible with many Linux distributions, leading to instant crashes on "
"startup. Fixed in C1022 and C1023."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3136
msgid ""
"CNAME referrals to child zones gave improper responses. Noted by Augie "
"Schwer in t123, fixed in c992."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3141
msgid ""
"When passing a port number with the <command>recursor</command> setting, "
"this would sometimes generate errors during additional processing. Switched "
"off overly helpful additional processing for recursive queries to remove "
"this problem. Implemented in c1031, spotted by Ralf van der Enden."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3147
msgid ""
"NS to a nameserver with the name of the zone itself generated "
"problems. Spotted by Augie Schwer, fixed in c947."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3152
msgid ""
"Multi-line records in the BIND backend were not always parsed "
"correctly. Fixed in c1014."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3157
msgid ""
"The LOC-record had problems operating outside of the eastern hemisphere of "
"the northern part of the world! Fixed in c1011."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3162
msgid ""
"Backends were compiled without multithreading preprocessor flags. As far as "
"we can determine, this would only cause problems for the BIND backend, but "
"we cannot rule out this caused instability in other backends. Fixed in "
"c1001."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3168
msgid ""
"The BIND backend was highly unstable under reloads, and leaked memory and "
"file descriptors.  Thanks to Mark Bergsma and Massimo Bandinelli for "
"respectively pointing this out to us and testing large amounts of patches to "
"fix the problem. The fixes have resulted in better performance, less code, "
"and a remarkable simplification of this backend. Commits C1039, C1034, "
"C1035, C1006, C999, C905 and previous."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3176
msgid ""
"BIND backend gave convincing NXDOMAINs on unloaded zones in some "
"cases. Spotted and fixed by Daniel Bilik in c984."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3181
msgid ""
"SOA records in zone transfers sometimes contained the wrong SOA TTL. Spotted "
"by Christian Kuehn, fixed in c902."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3186
msgid ""
"PowerDNS could get confused by very high SOA serial numbers. Spotted and "
"fixed by Dan Bilik, fixed in c626."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3191
msgid ""
"Some versions of FreeBSD perform very strict checks on socket address sizes "
"passed to 'connect', which could lead to problems retrieving zones over "
"AXFR.  Fixed in c891."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3197
msgid ""
"Some versions of FreeBSD perform very strict checks on IPv6 socket "
"addresses, leading to problems. Discovered by Sten Spans, fixed in c885 and "
"c886."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3202
msgid ""
"IXFR requests were not logged properly. Noted by Ralf van der Enden, fixed "
"in c990."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3207
msgid ""
"Some NAPTR records needed an additional space character to encode "
"correctly. Spotted by Heinrich Ruthensteiner, fixed in c1029."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3212
msgid ""
"Many bugs in the TCP nameserver, leading to a PowerDNS process that did not "
"respond to TCP queries over time. Many fixes provided by Dan Bilik, other "
"problems were fixed by rewriting our TCP handling code. Commits C982 and "
"C980, C950, C924, C889, C874, C869, C685, C684."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3218
msgid ""
"Fix crashes on the ARM processor due to alignment errors. Thanks to Sjoerd "
"Simons. Closes Debian bug 397031."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3223
msgid ""
"Missing data in generic SQL backends would sometimes lead to faked SOA "
"serial data. Spotted by Leander Lakkas from True. Fix in c866."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3228
msgid ""
"When receiving two quick notifications in succession, the packet cache would "
"sometimes \"process\" the second one, leading PowerDNS to ignore it. Spotted "
"by Dan Bilik, fixed in c686."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3234
msgid ""
"Geobackend (by Mark Bergsma) did not properly override the getSOA method, "
"breaking non-overlay operation of this fine backend. The geobackend now also "
"skips '.hidden' configuration files, and now properly disregards empty "
"configuration files. Additionally, the overlapping abilities were "
"improved. Details available in c876, by Mark."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3242 docs/pdns.xml:5479 docs/pdns.xml:6249 docs/pdns.xml:6448 docs/pdns.xml:6614 docs/pdns.xml:7058 docs/pdns.xml:7187 docs/pdns.xml:7428 docs/pdns.xml:7516 docs/pdns.xml:7599
