#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3385
msgid "Recursor version 3.1.4"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3387
msgid "Released the 13th of November 2006."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3390
msgid ""
"This release contains almost no new features, but consists mostly of minor "
"and major bug fixes. It also addresses two major security issues, which "
"makes this release a highly recommended upgrade."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3398
msgid ""
"Large TCP questions followed by garbage could cause the recursor to "
"crash. This critical security issue has been assigned CVE-2006-4251, and is "
"fixed in c915. More information can be found in <xref "
"linkend=\"powerdns-advisory-2006-01\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3404
msgid ""
"CNAME loops with zero second TTLs could cause crashes in some "
"conditions. These loops could be constructed by malicious parties, making "
"this issue a potential denial of service attack. This security issue has "
"been assigned CVE-2006-4252 and is fixed by c919.  More information can be "
"found in <xref linkend=\"powerdns-advisory-2006-02\"/>. Many thanks to David "
"Gavarret for helping pin down this problem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3416
msgid ""
"On certain error conditions, PowerDNS would neglect to close a socket, which "
"might therefore eventually run out. Spotted by Stefan Schmidt, fixed in "
"commits C892, C897, C899."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3421
msgid ""
"Some nameservers (including PowerDNS in rare circumstances) emit a SOA "
"record in the authority section. The recursor mistakenly interpreted this as "
"an authoritative \"NXRRSET\". Spotted by Bryan Seitz, fixed in c893."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3427
msgid ""
"In some circumstances, PowerDNS could end up with a useless (not working, or "
"no longer working) set of nameserver records for a domain. This release "
"contains logic to invalidate such broken NSSETs, without overloading "
"authoritative servers. This problem had previously been spotted by Bryan "
"Seitz, 'Cerb' and Darren Gamble.  Invalidations of NSSETs can be plotted "
"using the \"nsset-invalidations\" metric, available through "
"<command>rec_control get</command>.  Implemented in c896 and c901."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3435
msgid ""
"PowerDNS could crash while dumping the cache using <command>rec_control "
"dump-cache</command>. Reported by Wouter of WideXS and Stefan Schmidt and "
"many others, fixed in c900."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3440
msgid ""
"Under rare circumstances (depleted TCP buffers), PowerDNS might send out "
"incomplete questions to remote servers. Additionally, on big-endian systems "
"(non-Intel and non-AMD generally), sending out large TCP answers questions "
"would not work at all, and possibly crash. Brought to our attention by David "
"Gavarret, fixed in c903."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3446
msgid ""
"The recursor contained the potential for a dead-lock processing an invalid "
"domain name. It is not known how this might be triggered, but it has been "
"observed by 'Cerb' on #powerdns. Several dead-locks where PowerDNS consumed "
"all CPU, but did not answer questions, have been reported in the past few "
"months. These might be fixed by c904."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3453
msgid ""
"IPv6 'allow-from' matching had problems with the least significant bits, "
"sometimes allowing disallowed addresses, but mostly disallowing allowed "
"addresses. Spotted by Wouter from WideXS, fixed in c916."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3463
msgid ""
"PowerDNS has support to drop answers from so called 'delegation only' "
"zones. A statistic (\"dlg-only-drops\") is now available to plot how often "
"this happens. Implemented in c890."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3468
msgid ""
"Hint-file parameter was mistakenly named \"hints-file\" in the "
"documentation. Spotted by my Marco Davids, fixed in c898."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3473
msgid ""
"<command>rec_control quit</command> should be near instantaneous now, as it "
"no longer meticulously cleans up memory before exiting. Problem spotted by "
"Darren Gamble, fixed in c914, closing t84."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3479
msgid ""
"init.d script no longer refers to the Recursor as the Authoritative "
"Server. Spotted by Wouter of WideXS, fixed in c913."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3484
msgid ""
"A potentially serious warning for users of the GNU C Library version 2.5 was "
"fixed. Spotted by Marcus Rueckert, fixed in c920."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3491
msgid "Recursor version 3.1.3"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3493
msgid "Released the 12th of September 2006."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3496
msgid ""
"Compared to 3.1.2, this release again consists of a number of mostly minor "
"bug fixes, and some slight improvements."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3499
msgid ""
"Many thanks are again due to Darren Gamble who together with his team has "
"discovered many misconfigured domains that do work with some other name "
"servers. DNS has long been tolerant of misconfigurations, PowerDNS intends "
"to uphold that tradition. Almost all of the domains found by Darren now work "
"as well in PowerDNS as in other name server implementations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3504
msgid ""
"Thanks to some recent migrations, this release, or something very close to "
"it, is powering over 40 million internet connections that we know of. We "
"appreciate hearing about successful as well as unsuccessful migrations, "
"please feel free to notify pdns.bd@powerdns.com of your experiences, good or "
"bad."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3509 docs/pdns.xml:3575
msgid "Bug-fixes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3513
msgid ""
"The MThread default stack size was too small, which led to problems, mostly "
"on 64-bit platforms. This stack size is now configurable using the "
"<command>stack-size</command> setting should our estimate be off. Discovered "
"by Darren Gamble, Sten Spans and a number of others.  Fixed in c868."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3520
msgid "Plug a small memory leak discovered by Kai and Darren Gamble, fixed in c870."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3525
msgid ""
"Switch from the excellent nedmalloc to dlmalloc, based on advice by the "
"nedmalloc author. Nedmalloc is optimised for multithreaded operation, "
"whereas the PowerDNS recursor is single threaded. The version of nedmalloc "
"shipped contained a number of possible bugs, which are probably resolved by "
"moving to dlmalloc. Some reported crashes on hitting 2G of allocated memory "
"on 64 bit systems might be solved by this switch, which should also increase "
"performance. See c873 for details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3538
msgid ""
"The cache is now explicitly aware of the difference between authoritative "
"and unauthoritative data, allowing it to deal with some domains that have "
"different data in the parent zone than in the authoritative zone. Patch in "
"c867."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3544
msgid ""
"No longer try to parse DNS updates as if they were queries. Discovered and "
"fixed by Jan Gyselinck, fix in c871."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3549
msgid ""
"Rebalance logging priorities for less log cluttering and add IP address to a "
"remote server error message.  Noticed and fixed by Jan Gyselinck (c877)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3555
msgid ""
"Add <command>logging-facility</command> setting, allowing syslog to send "
"PowerDNS logging to a separate file. Added in c871."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3561
msgid "Recursor version 3.1.2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3563
msgid "Released Monday 26th of June 2006."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3566
msgid ""
"Compared to 3.1.1, this release consists almost exclusively of bug-fixes and "
"speedups. A quick update is recommended, as some of the bugs impact "
"operators of authoritative zones on the internet. This version has been "
"tested by some of the largest internet providers on the planet, and is "
"expected to perform well for everybody."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3571
msgid ""
"Many thanks are due to Darren Gamble, Stefan Schmidt and Bryan Seitz who all "
"provided excellent feedback based on their large-scale tests of the "
"recursor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3579
msgid ""
"Internal authoritative server did not differentiate between 'NXDOMAIN' and "
"'NXRRSET', in other words, it would answer 'no such host' when an AAAA query "
"came in for a domain that did exist, but did not have an AAAA record. This "
"only affects users with <command>auth-zones</command> configured. Discovered "
"by Bryan Seitz, fixed in c848."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3586
msgid ""
"ANY queries for hosts where nothing was present in the cache would not "
"work. This did not cause real problems as ANY queries are not reliable (by "
"design) for anything other than debugging, but did slow down the nameserver "
"and cause unnecessary load on remote nameservers. Fixed in c854."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3593
msgid ""
"When exceeding the configured maximum amount of TCP sessions, TCP support "
"would break and the nameserver would waste CPU trying to accept TCP "
"connections on UDP ports. Noted by Bryan Seitz, fixed in c849."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3599
msgid ""
"DNS queries come in two flavours: recursion desired and non-recursion "
"desired. The latter is not very useful for a recursor, but is sometimes "
"(erroneously) used by monitoring software or load balancers to detect "
"nameserver availability. A non-rd query would not only not recurse, but also "
"not query authoritative zones, which is confusing. Fixed in c847."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3606
msgid ""
"Non-standard DNS TCP queries, that did occur however, could drive the "
"recursor to 100% CPU usage for extended periods of time. This did not "
"disrupt service immediately, but does waste a lot of CPU, possibly "
"exhausting resources. Discovered by Bryan Seitz, fixed in c858, which is "
"post-3.1.2-rc1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3612
msgid ""
"The PowerDNS recursor did not honour the rare but standardised 'ANY' query "
"class (normally 'ANY' refers to the query type, not class), upsetting the "
"Wildfire Jabber server. Discovered and debugged by Daniel Nauck, fixed in "
"c859, which is post-3.1.2-rc1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3618
msgid ""
"Everybody's favorite, when starting up under high load, a bogus line of "
"statistics was sometimes logged. Fixed in c851."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3623
msgid ""
"Remove some spurious debugging output on dropping a packet by an "
"unauthorized host. Discovered by Kai. Fixed in c854."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3633
msgid ""
"Misconfigured domains, with a broken nameserver in the parent zone, should "
"now work better. Changes motivated and suggested by Darren Gamble. This "
"makes PowerDNS more compliant with RFC 2181 by making it prefer "
"authoritative data over non-authoritative data.  Implemented in c856."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3640
msgid ""
"PowerDNS can now listen on multiple ports, using the "
"<command>local-address</command> setting. Added in c845."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3645
msgid ""
"A number of speedups which should have a noticeable impact, implemented in "
"commits C850, C852, C853, C855"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3650
msgid ""
"The recursor now works around an issue with the Linux kernel 2.6.8, as "
"shipped by Debian. Fixed by Christof Meerwald in c860, which is post "
"3.1.2-rc1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3656
msgid "Recursor version 3.1.1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3660
msgid ""
"3.1.1 is identical to 3.1 except for a bug in the packet chaining code which "
"would mainly manifest itself for IPv6 enabled Konqueror users with very fast "
"connections to their PowerDNS installation. However, all 3.1 users are urged "
"to upgrade to 3.1.1.  Many thanks to Alessandro Bono for his quick aid in "
"solving this problem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3667
msgid ""
"Released on the 23rd of May 2006. Many thanks are due to the operators of "
"some of the largest internet access providers in the world, each having many "
"millions of customers, who have tested the various 3.1 pre-releases for "
"suitability. They have uncovered and helped fix bugs that could impact us "
"all, but are only (quickly) noticeable with such vast amounts of DNS "
"traffic."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3672
msgid ""
"After version 3.0.1 has proved to hold up very well under tremendous loads, "
"3.1 adds important new features:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3676
msgid ""
"Ability to serve authoritative data from 'BIND' style zone files (using "
"<command>auth-zones</command> statement)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3681
msgid ""
"Ability to forward domains so configured to external servers (using "
"<command>forward-zones</command>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3686
msgid ""
"Possibility of 'serving' the contents of <filename>/etc/hosts</filename> "
"over DNS, which is very well suited to simple domestic router/DNS "
"setups. Enabled using <command>export-etc-hosts</command>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3692
msgid ""
"As recommended by recent standards documents, the PowerDNS recursor is now "
"authoritative for RFC-1918 private IP space zones by default (suggested by "
"Paul Vixie)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3698
msgid ""
"Full outgoing IPv6 support (off by default) with IPv6 servers getting equal "
"treatment with IPv4, nameserver addresses are chosen based on average "
"response speed, irrespective of protocol."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3704
msgid ""
"Initial Windows support, including running as a service ('NET START "
"\"POWERDNS RECURSOR\"'). <command>rec_channel</command> is still missing, "
"the rest should work. Performance appears to be below that of the UNIX "
"versions, this situation is expected to improve."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3715
msgid ""
"No longer send out SRV and MX record priorities as zero on big-endian "
"platforms (UltraSPARC). Discovered by Eric Sproul, fixed in c773."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3720
msgid ""
"SRV records need additional processing, especially in an Active Directory "
"setting. Reported by Kenneth Marshall, fixed in c774."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3725
msgid ""
"The root-records were not being refreshed, which could lead to problems "
"under inconceivable conditions. Fixed in c780."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3730
msgid ""
"Fix resolving domain names for nameservers with multiple IP addresses, with "
"one of these addresses being lame. Other nameserver implementations were "
"also unable to resolve these domains, so not a big bug. Fixed in c780."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3736
msgid ""
"For a period of 5 minutes after expiring a negative cache entry, the domain "
"would not be re-cached negatively, leading to a lot of duplicate outgoing "
"queries for this short period. This fix has raised the average cache hit "
"rate of the recursor by a few percent. Fixed in c783."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3743
msgid ""
"Query throttling was not aggressive enough and not all sorts of queries were "
"throttled. Implemented in c786."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3749
msgid ""
"Fix possible crash during startup when parsing empty configuration lines "
"(c807)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3754
msgid ""
"Fix possible crash when the first query after wiping a cache entry was for "
"the just deleted entry. Rare in production servers. Fixed in c820."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3759
msgid ""
"Recursor would send out differing TTLs when receiving a misconfigured, "
"standards violating, RRSET with different TTLs. Implement fix as mandated by "
"RFC 2181, paragraph 5.2. Reported by Stephen Harker (c819)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3765
msgid ""
"The <command>top-remotes</command> would list remotes more than once, once "
"per source port. Discovered by Jorn Ekkelenkamp, fixed in c827, which is "
"post 3.1-pre1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3770
msgid ""
"Default <command>allow-from</command> allowed queries from fe80::/16, "
"corrected to fe80::/10. Spotted by Niels Bakker, fixed in c829, which is "
"post 3.1-pre1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3775
msgid ""
"While PowerDNS blocks failing queries quickly, multiple packets could "
"briefly be in flight for the same domain and nameserver. This situation is "
"now explicitly detected and queries are chained to identical queries already "
"in flight. Fixed in c833 and c834, post 3.1-pre1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3786
msgid ""
"ANY queries are now implemented as in other nameserver implementations, "
"leading to a decrease in outgoing queries. The RFCs are not very clear on "
"desired behaviour, what is implemented now saves bandwidth and CPU and "
"brings us in line with existing practice. Previously ANY queries were not "
"cached by the PowerDNS recursor. Implemented in c784."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3793
msgid ""
"<command>rec_control</command> was very sparse in its error reporting, and "
"user unfriendly as well. Reported by Erik Bos, fixed in c818 and c820."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3798
msgid "IPv6 addresses were printed in a non-standard way, fixed in c788."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3803
msgid "TTLs of records are now capped at two weeks, c820."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3808
msgid ""
"<command>allow-from</command> IPv4 netmasks now automatically work for "
"IP4-to-IPv6 mapper IPv4 addresses, which appear when running on the wildcard "
"<command>::</command> IPv6 address. Lack of feature noted by Marcus 'darix' "
"Rueckert. Fixed in c826, which is post 3.1-pre1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3814
msgid ""
"Errors before daemonizing are now also sent to syslog. Suggested by Marcus "
"'darix' Rueckert. Fixed in c825, which is post 3.1-pre1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3819
msgid ""
"When launching without any form of configured network connectivity, all "
"root-servers would be cached as 'down' for some time. Detect this special "
"case and treat it as a resource-constraint, which is not accounted against "
"specific nameservers. Spotted by Seth Arnold, fixed in c835, which is post "
"3.1-pre1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3825
msgid ""
"The recursor now does not allow authoritative servers to keep supplying its "
"own NS records into perpetuity, which causes problems when a domain is "
"redelegated but the old authoritative servers are not updated to this "
"effect. Noticed and explained at length by Darren Gamble of Shaw "
"Communications, addressed by c837, which is post 3.1-pre2."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3832
msgid ""
"Some operators may want to follow RFC 2181 paragraph 5.2 and 5.4. This harms "
"performance and does not solve any real problem, but does make PowerDNS more "
"compliant. If you want this, enable "
"<command>auth-can-lower-ttl</command>. Implemented in c838, which is post "
"3.1-pre2."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3840
msgid "Recursor version 3.0.1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3842
msgid ""
"Released 25th of April 2006, <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.powerdns.com/en/downloads.aspx\">download</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3845
msgid ""
"This release consists of nothing but tiny fixes to 3.0, including one with "
"security implications. An upgrade is highly recommended."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3851
msgid ""
"Compilation used both <filename>cc</filename> and <filename>gcc</filename>, "
"leading to the possibility of compiling with different compiler versions "
"(c766)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3856
msgid ""
"<command>rec_control</command> would leave files named "
"<filename>lsockXXXXXX</filename> around in the configured "
"socket-dir. Operators may wish to remove these files from their socket-dir "
"(often <filename>/var/run</filename>), quite a few might have accumulated "
"already (c767)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3863
msgid ""
"Certain malformed packets could crash the recursor. As far as we can "
"determine these packets could only lead to a crash, but as always, there are "
"no guarantees. A quick upgrade is highly recommended (commits C760, "
"C761). Reported by David Gavarret."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3870
msgid ""
"Recursor would not distinguish between NXDOMAIN and NXRRSET (c756). Reported "
"and debugged by Jorn Ekkelenkamp."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3875
msgid ""
"Some error messages and trace logging statements were improved (commits "
"C756, C758, C759)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3880
msgid ""
"stderr was closed during daemonizing, but not dupped to /dev/null, leading "
"to slight chance of odd behaviour on reporting errors (c757)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3884
msgid "Operating system specific fixes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3888
msgid ""
"The stock Debian sarge Linux kernel, 2.6.8, claims to support epoll but "
"fails at runtime. The epoll self-testing code has been improved, and "
"PowerDNS will fall back to a select based multiplexer if needed (c758) "
"Reported by Michiel van Es."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3894
msgid ""
"Solaris 8 compilation and runtime issues were addressed. See the README for "
"details (c765). Reported by Juergen Georgi and Kenneth Marshall."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3899
msgid ""
"Solaris 10 x86_64 compilation issues were addressed (c755). Reported and "
"debugged by Eric Sproul."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3905
msgid "Recursor version 3.0"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3907
msgid ""
"Released 20th of April 2006, <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.powerdns.com/en/downloads.aspx\">download</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3910
msgid ""
"This is the first separate release of the PowerDNS Recursor. There are many "
"reasons for this, one of the most important ones is that previously we could "
"only do a release when both the recursor and the authoritative nameserver "
"were fully tested and in good shape. The split allows us to release new "
"versions when each part is ready."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3915
msgid ""
"Now for the real news. This version of the PowerDNS recursor powers the "
"network access of over two million internet connections. Two large access "
"providers have been running pre-releases of 3.0 for the past few weeks and "
"results are good. Furthermore, the various pre-releases have been tested "
"nearly non-stop with DNS traffic replayed at 3000 queries/second."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3920
msgid ""
"As expected, the 2 million households shook out some very rare bugs. But "
"even a rare bug happens once in a while when there are this many users."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3923
msgid ""
"We consider this version of the PowerDNS recursor to be the most advanced "
"resolver publicly available. Given current levels of spam, phishing and "
"other forms of internet crime we think no recursor should offer less than "
"the best in spoofing protection. We urge all operators of resolvers without "
"proper spoofing countermeasures to consider PowerDNS, as it is a Better "
"Internet Nameserver Daemon."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3928
msgid ""
"A good article on DNS spoofing can be found <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.securesphere.net/download/papers/dnsspoof.htm\">here</ulink>. "
"Some more information, based on a previous version of PowerDNS, can be found "
"on the <ulink "
"url=\"http://blog.netherlabs.nl/articles/2006/04/14/holy-cow-1-3-million-additional-ip-addresses-served-by-powerdns\">PowerDNS "
"development blog</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3935
msgid ""
"Because of recent DNS based denial of service attacks, running an open "
"recursor has become a security risk. Therefore, unless configured otherwise "
"this version of PowerDNS will only listen on localhost, which means it does "
"not resolve for hosts on your network.  To fix, configure the "
"<command>local-address</command> setting with all addresses you want to "
"listen on. Additionally, by default service is restricted to RFC 1918 "
"private IP addresses. Use <command>allow-from</command> to selectively open "
"up the recursor for your own network. See <xref "
"linkend=\"recursor-settings\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3944
msgid "Important new features of the PowerDNS recursor 3.0:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3948
msgid ""
"Best spoofing protection and detection we know of. Not only is spoofing made "
"harder by using a new network address for each query, PowerDNS detects when "
"an attempt is made to spoof it, and temporarily ignores the data. For "
"details, see <xref linkend=\"anti-spoofing\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3954
msgid ""
"First nameserver to benefit from epoll/kqueue/Solaris completion ports event "
"reporting framework, for stellar performance."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3959
msgid ""
"Best statistics of any recursing nameserver we know of, see <xref "
"linkend=\"recursor-stats\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3964
msgid ""
"Last-recently-used based cache cleanup algorithm, keeping the 'best' records "
"in memory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3969
msgid ""
"First class Solaris support, built on a 'try and buy' Sun CoolThreads "
"T&nbsp;2000."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3974
msgid "Full IPv6 support, implemented natively."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3979
msgid "Access filtering, both for IPv4 and IPv6."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3984
msgid ""
"Experimental SMP support for nearly double performance. See <xref "
"linkend=\"recursor-performance\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3990
msgid ""
"Many people helped package and test this release. Jorn Ekkelenkamp of "
"ISP-Services helped find the '8000 SOAs' bug and spotted many other oddities "
"and <ulink url=\"http://www.xs4all.nl\">XS4ALL</ulink> internet funded a lot "
"of the recent development.  Joaqu&iacute;n M L&oacute;pez Mu&ntilde;oz of "
"the boost::multi_index_container was again of great help."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3995
msgid "Version 2.9.20"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:3997
msgid "Released the 15th of March 2006"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4000
msgid ""
"Besides adding OpenDBX, this release is mostly about fixing problems and "
"speeding up the recursor. This release has been made possible by <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.xs4all.nl\">XS4ALL</ulink> and <ulink "
"url=\"http://true.nl\">True</ulink>. Thanks!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4004
msgid ""
"Furthermore, we are very grateful for the help of Andrew Pinski, who hacks "
"on gcc, and of Joaqu&iacute;n M L&oacute;pez Mu&ntilde;oz, the author of "
"<ulink "
"url=\"http://www.boost.org/libs/multi_index/doc/index.html\">boost::multi_index_container</ulink>. "
"Without their near-realtime help this release would've been delayed a "
"lot. Thanks!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4009
msgid "Bugs fixed in the recursor:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4013
msgid ""
"Possible stability issues in the recursor on encountering errors (c532, "
"c533)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4018
msgid ""
"Memory leaks in recursor fixed (c534, c572). In a test 800 million real life "
"DNS packets have been sent to the recursor, representing several days of "
"traffic from a major ISP, memory use was high (500MB), but stable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4024
msgid ""
"Prune all data in PowerDNS - previously per-nameserver and per-query "
"performance statistics were kept around forever (c535)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4030
msgid ""
"IPv6 additional processing was broken. Reported by Lionel Elie Mamane, who "
"also provided a fix. The problem was fixed differently in the end. c562."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4036
msgid ""
"pdns_recursor did not shuffle answers since 2.9.19, leading to problems "
"sending mail to the Hotmail servers.  Reported in t54, fixed in c567."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4042
msgid ""
"If a single nameserver had multiple IP addresses listed, PowerDNS would only "
"use one of them. Noted by Mark Martin, fixed in c570, who depends on a "
"domain with 4 nameserver IP addresses of which 2 are broken."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4051
msgid "Improvements to the recursor:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4055
msgid ""
"Commits C535, C540, C541, C542, C543, C544, C545, C547 and C548, C574 all "
"speed up the recursor by a large factor, without altering the DNS algorithm."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4061
msgid ""
"Move recursor to the incredible boost::multi_index_container (c580). This "
"brings a huge improvement in cache pruning times."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4067
msgid ""
"c549 and c550 work around gcc bug <ulink "
"url=\"http://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=24704\">24704</ulink> if "
"requested, which speeds up the recursor a lot, but involves a dirty "
"hack. Enable with <command>./configure "
"--enable-gcc-skip-locking</command>. No guarantees!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4074
msgid "Bugs fixed in the authoritative nameserver:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4078
msgid ""
"PowerDNS would no longer allow a '/' in domain names, fixed by c537, "
"reported in t48."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4083
msgid ""
"Parameters to <command>pdns_control notify-host</command> were not checked, "
"leading to possible crashes. Reported in t24, fixed in c565."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4089
msgid ""
"On some compilers, processing of NAPTR records could cause the server to "
"crash. Reported by Bernd Froemel in t29, fixed in c538."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4095
msgid ""
"Backend errors could make the whole nameserver exit under some "
"circumstances, notably using the LDAP backend. Fixed in c583, reported in "
"t62."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4101
msgid ""
"Referrals were subtly broken by recent CNAME/Wildcard improvements, fixed in "
"c539. Fix and other improvements sponsored by <ulink "
"url=\"http://true.nl\">True</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4107
msgid ""
"PowerDNS would try to insert records it has no knowledge about in slave "
"zones, which did not work. Reported in t60, fixed in c566. A superior fix "
"would be to implement the relevant unknown record standard."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:4112
