"next release - this won't happen now."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5695
msgid ""
"However, this turns out to not be that bad at all. The recursor can now be "
"restarted without having to restart the rest of the nameserver, for "
"example. Cooperation between the both halves of PDNS is also almost "
"seamless. As a result, 'non-lazy recursion' has been dropped. See <xref "
"linkend=\"recursion\"/> for more details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5700
msgid ""
"Furthermore, the recursor only works on Linux, Windows and Solaris (not "
"entirely). FreeBSD does not support the required functions.  If you know any "
"important FreeBSD people, plea with them to support set/get/swapcontext! "
"Alternatively, FreeBSD coders could read the solution presented here <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.eng.uwaterloo.ca/~ejones/software/threading.html\">in "
"figure 5</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5705
msgid ""
"The 'Contributor of the Month' award goes to Mark Bergsma who has responded "
"to our plea for help with the label compressor and contributed a wonderfully "
"simple and right fix that allows PDNS to compress just as well as other "
"nameservers out there. An honorary mention goes to Ueli Heuer who, despite "
"having no C++ experience, submitted an excellent SRV record implementation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5710
msgid ""
"Excellent work was also performed by Michel Stol, the Windows guy, in fixing "
"all our non-portable stuff again. Christof Meerwald has also done wonderful "
"work in porting MTasker to Windows, which was then used by Michel to get the "
"recursor functioning on Windows."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5718
msgid "dnspacket.cc was cleaned up by factoring out common operations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5723
msgid ""
"Heaps of work on the recursing nameserver. Has now achieved *days* of "
"uptime!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5728
msgid "Recursor renamed from syncres to <filename>pdns_recursor</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5733
msgid ""
"PowerDNS can now serve records it does not know about. To benefit from this "
"slightly undocumented feature, add 1024 to the numerical type of a record "
"and include the record in binary form in your database. Used internally by "
"the recursing nameserver but you can use it too."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5740
msgid ""
"PowerDNS now knows about SIG and KEY records *names*. It does not support "
"them yet but can at least report so now."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5745
msgid ""
"HINFO records can now be transferred from a master to PowerDNS (thanks to "
"Ueli Heuer for noticing it didn't work)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5750
msgid "Yet more UltraSPARC alignment issues fixed (Chris Andrews)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5755
msgid ""
"Dropped non-lazy recursion, nobody was using it. Lazy recursion became even "
"more lazy after Dan Bernstein pointed out that additional processing is not "
"vital, so PowerDNS does its best to do additional processing on recursive "
"queries, but does not scream murder if it does not succeed. Due to caching, "
"the next identical query will be successfully additionally processed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5762
msgid ""
"Label compression was improved so we can now fit all . records in 436 bytes, "
"this used to be 460! (Code &amp; formal proof of correctness by Mark "
"Bergsma)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5768
msgid "SRV support (incoming and outgoing), submitted by Ueli Heuer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5773
msgid ""
"Generic backends do not support SOA serial autocalculation, it "
"appears. Could lead to random SOA serials in case of a serial of 0 in the "
"database. Fixed so that 0 stays zero in that case. Don't set the SOA serial "
"to 0 when using Generic MySQL or Generic PostgreSQL!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5780
msgid "J root-server address was updated to its new location."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5785
msgid "SIGUSR1 now forces the recursor to print out statistics to the log."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5790
msgid ""
"Meaning of recursor logging was changed a bit - a cache hit is now a "
"question that was answered with 0 outgoing packets needed. Used to be a "
"weighted average of internal cache hits."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5796
msgid ""
"MySQL compilation did not include -lz which causes problems on some "
"platforms. Thanks to James H. Cloos Jr for reporting this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5801
msgid ""
"After a suggestion by Daniel Meyer and Florus Both, the built in webserver "
"now reports the configuration name when multiple PowerDNS instances are "
"active."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5807
msgid ""
"Brad Knowles noticed that zone2sql had problems with the root.zone, "
"fixed. This also closes some other zone2sql annoyances with converting "
"single zones."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5815
msgid "Version 2.9.4"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5817
msgid ""
"Yet another grand release. Big news is the addition of a recursing "
"nameserver which has sprung into existence over the past week. It is in use "
"on several computers already but it is not ready for prime time. Complete "
"integration with PowerDNS is expected around 2.9.5, for now the recursor is "
"a separate program."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5822
msgid ""
"In preliminary tests, the recursor appears to be four times faster than BIND "
"9 on a naive benchmark starting from a cold cache. BIND 9 managed to get "
"through to some slower nameservers however, which were given up on by "
"PowerDNS. We will continue to tune the recursor.  See <xref "
"linkend=\"built-in-recursor\"/> for further details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5827
msgid ""
"The BIND Backend has also been tested (see the "
"<command>bind-domain-status</command> item below) rather heavily by several "
"parties. After some discussion online, one of the BIND authors ventured that "
"the newsgroup comp.protocols.dns.bind may now in fact be an appropriate "
"venue for discussing PowerDNS. Since this discussion, traffic to the "
"PowerDNS pages has increased sixfold and shows no signs of slowing down."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5832
msgid ""
"From this, it is apparent that far more people are interested in PowerDNS "
"than yet know about it. So spread the word!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5835
msgid ""
"In other news, we now have a security page at <xref "
"linkend=\"security-policy\"/>. Furthermore, Maurice Nonnekes contributed an "
"OpenBSD port! See <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.codeninja.nl/openbsd/powerdns/\">his page</ulink> for more "
"details!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5839
msgid "New features and improvements:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5843
msgid ""
"All SQL queries in the generic backends are now available for "
"configuration. (Martin Klebermass, Bert Hubert).  See <xref "
"linkend=\"generic-mypgsql-backends\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5849
msgid "A recursing nameserver! See <xref linkend=\"built-in-recursor\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5854
msgid ""
"An incoming AXFR now only starts a backend zone replacement transaction "
"after the first record arrived successfully, thus making sure no work is "
"done when a remote nameserver is unable/unwilling to AXFR a zone to us."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5860
msgid ""
"Zone parser error messages were improved slightly (thanks to Stef van Dessel "
"for spotting this shortcoming)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5865
msgid ""
"XS4ALL's Erik Bos checked how PowerDNS reacted to a BIND installation with "
"almost 60.000 domains, some of which with >100.000 records, and he "
"discovered the pdns_control <command>bind-domain-status</command> command "
"became very slow with larger numbers of domains. Fixed, 60.000 domains are "
"now listed in under one second."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5872
msgid ""
"If a remote nameserver disconnects during an incoming AXFR, the update is "
"now rolled back, unless the AXFR was properly terminated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5878
msgid "The migration chapter mentioned the use of deprecated backends."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5884
msgid "A tremendous number of bugs were discovered and fixed:"
msgstr ""

