#: docs/pdns.xml:5888
msgid "Zone parser would only accept $include and not $INCLUDE"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5893
msgid "Zone parser had problems with $lines with comments on the end"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5898
msgid "Wildcard ANY queries were broken (thanks Colemarcus for spotting this)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5903
msgid ""
"A connection failure with the Generic backends would lead to a powerdns "
"reload (cast of many)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5908
msgid ""
"Generic backends had some semantic problems with slave support. Symptoms "
"were oft-repeated notifications and transfers (thanks to Mark Bergsma for "
"helping resolve this)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5914
msgid ""
"Solaris version compiles again. Thanks to Mohamed Lrhazi for reporting that "
"it didn't."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5919
msgid ""
"Some UltraSPARC alignment fixes. Thanks to Mohamed Lrhazi for being helpful "
"in spotting these.  One problem is still outstanding, Mohamed sent a core "
"dump that tells us where the problem is. Expect the fix to be in "
"2.9.5. Volunteers can grep the source for 'UltraSPARC' to find where the "
"problem is."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5926
msgid ""
"Our support of IPv6 on FreeBSD had phase of moon dependent bugs, fixed by "
"Peter van Dijk."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5931
msgid ""
"Some crashes of and by pdns_control were fixed, thanks to Mark Bergsma for "
"helping resolve these."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5936
msgid ""
"Outgoing AXFR in pdns installations with multiple loaded backends was broken "
"(thanks to Stuart Walsh for reporting this)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5941
msgid ""
"A failed BIND Backend incoming AXFR would block the zone until it succeeded "
"again."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5946
msgid ""
"Generic PostgreSQL backend wouldn't compile with newer libpq++, fixed by "
"Julien Lemoine/SpeedBlue."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5951
msgid "Potential bug (not observed) when listening on multiple interfaces fixed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:5956
msgid "Some typos in manpages fixed (reported by Marco Davids)."
