#: docs/pdns.xml:5979
msgid ""
"After the SOA of ds9a.nl was raised: <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/> "
"If however our slaves would ignore us, as some are prone to do, we can send "
"some additional notifications: <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"1\"/> "
"Conversely, if PowerDNS needs to be reminded to retrieve a zone from a "
"master, a command is provided: <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"2\"/> Also, "
"you can force PowerDNS to reload a zone from disk immediately with "
"<command>pdns_control bind-reload-now</command>.  All this happens 'live', "
"per your instructions. Without instructions, the right things also happen, "
"but the operator is in charge."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6015
msgid ""
"For more about all this coolness, see <xref linkend=\"pdnscontrol\"/> and "
"<xref linkend=\"bind-control-commands\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6020
msgid ""
"Again some changes in compilation instructions. The hybrid pgmysql backend "
"has been split up into 'gmysql' and 'gpgsql', sharing a common base within "
"the PowerDNS server itself. This means that you can no longer compile "
"<command>--with-modules=\"pgmysql\" --enable-mysql --enable-pgsql</command> "
"but that you should now use: <command>--with-modules=\"gmysql "
"gpgsql\"</command>. The old launch-names remain available."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6026
msgid ""
"If you launch the Generic PgSQL backend as gpgsql2, all parameters will have "
"gpgsql2 as a prefix, for example <command>gpgsql2-dbname</command>. If "
"launched as gpgsql, the regular names are in effect."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6034
msgid ""
"The pdns_control protocol was changed which means that older pdns_controls "
"cannot talk to 2.9.3. The other way around is broken too. This may lead to "
"problems with automatic upgrade scripts, so pay attention if your daemon is "
"truly restarted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6038
msgid "Also make sure no old pdns_control command is around to confuse things."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6047
msgid "Bind backend can now deal with missing files and try to find them later."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6052
msgid ""
"Bind backend is now explicitly master capable and triggers the sending of "
"notifications."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6057
msgid ""
"General robustness improvements in Bind backend - many errors are now "
"non-fatal."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6062
msgid ""
"Accessibility, Serviceability. New <command>pdns_server</command> commands "
"like <command>bind-list-rejects</command> (lists zones that could not be "
"loaded, and the reason why), <command>bind-reload-now</command> (reload a "
"zone from disk NOW), <command>rediscover</command> (reread named.conf "
"NOW). More is coming up."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6069
msgid ""
"Added support for retrieving RP (Responsible Person) records from remote "
"masters. Serving them was already possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6074
msgid ""
"Added support for LOC records, which encode the geographical location of a "
"host, both serving and retrieving (thanks to Marco Davids using them on our "
"last Bind server, forcing us to implement this silly record)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6080
msgid ""
"Configuration file parser now strips leading spaces too, allowing \"chroot= "
"/tmp\" to work, as well as \"chroot=/tmp\" (Thanks to Hub Dohmen for "
"reporting this for months on end)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6086
msgid ""
"Added <command>bind-domain-status</command> command that shows the status of "
"all domains (when/if they were parsed, any errors encountered while parsing "
"them)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6092
msgid ""
"Added <command>bind-reload-now</command> command that tries to reload a zone "
"from disk NOW, and reports back errors to the operator immediately."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6098
msgid ""
"Added <command>retrieve</command> command that queues a request to retrieve "
"a zone from its master."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6103
msgid ""
"Zones retrieved from masters are now stored way smaller on disk because the "
"domain is stripped from records, which is derived from the configuration "
"file. Retrieved zones are now prefixed with some information on where they "
"came from."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6110 docs/pdns.xml:6306
msgid "Changes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6114
msgid ""
"gpgsql and gmysql backends split out of the hybrid pgmysqlbackend. This "
"again changed compilation instructions!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6119
msgid ""
"<command>pdns_control</command> now uses the rarely seen SOCK_STREAM Unix "
"Domain socket variety so it can transport large amounts of text, which is "
"needed for the <command>bind-domain-status</command> command, for which see "
"<xref linkend=\"bind-control-commands\"/>. This breaks compatibility with "
"older pdns_control and pdns_server binaries!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6126
msgid ""
"Bind backend now ignores 'hint' and 'forward' and other unsupported zone "
"types."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6131
msgid ""
"AXFRs are now logged more heavily by default. An AXFR is a heavy operation "
"anyhow, some more logging does not further increase the load "
"materially. Does help in clearing up what slaves are doing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6137
msgid ""
