#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6444
msgid ""
"This version fixes some very long standing issues and adds a few new "
"features. If you are still running 2.6, upgrade yesterday. If you were "
"running 2.6.1, an upgrade is still strongly advised."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6452
msgid ""
"The controlsocket is now readable and writable by the 'setgid' user. This "
"allows for non-root access to PDNS which is nice for mrtg or cricket graphs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6458
msgid ""
"MySQL backend (the non-generic one) gains the ability to read from a "
"different table using the <command>mysql-table</command> setting."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6464
msgid ""
"pipe backend now has a configurable timeout using the "
"<command>pipe-timeout</command> setting. Thanks to Steve Bromwich for "
"pointing out the need for this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6470
msgid ""
"Experimental backtraces. If PowerDNS crashes, it will log a lot of numbers "
"and sometimes more to the syslog.  If you see these, please report them to "
"us. Only available under Linux."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6481
msgid ""
"2.7 briefly broke the mysql backend, so don't use it if you use that. 2.7.1 "
"fixes this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6486
msgid ""
"SOA records could sometimes have the wrong TTL. Thanks to Jonas Daugaard for "
"reporting this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6491
msgid ""
"An ANY query might lead to duplicate SOA records being returned under "
"exceptional circumstances.  Thanks to Jonas Daugaard for reporting this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6497
msgid ""
"Underlying the above bug, packet compression could sometimes suddenly be "
"turned off, leading to overly large responses and non-removal of duplicate "
"records."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6503
msgid ""
"The <command>allow-axfr-ips</command> setting did not accept IP ranges "
"(1.2.3.0/24) which the documentation claimed it did (thanks to Florus Both "
"of Ascio technologies for being sufficiently persistent in reporting this)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6509
msgid ""
"Killed backends were not being respawned, leading to suboptimal behaviour on "
"intermittent database errors. Thanks to Steve Bromwich for reporting this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6515
msgid ""
"Corrupt packets during an incoming AXFR when acting as a slave would cause a "
"PowerDNS reload instead of just failing that AXFR.  Thanks to Mike Benoit "
"and Simon Kirby of NetNation for reporting this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6521
msgid ""
"Label compression in incoming AXFR had problems with large offsets, causing "
"the above mentioned errors. Thanks to Mike Benoit and Simon Kirby of "
"NetNation for reporting this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6529
msgid "Version 2.6.1"
