#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6534
msgid "Version 2.6"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6536
msgid ""
"Performance release. A lot of work has been done to raise PDNS performance "
"to staggering levels in order to take part in benchmarketing "
"efforts. Together with our as yet unnamed partner, PDNS has been benchmarked "
"at 60.000 mostly cached queries/second on off the shelf PC "
"hardware. Uncached performance was 17.000 uncached DNS queries/second on the "
".ORG domain."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6541
msgid ""
"Performance has been increased by both making PDNS itself quicker but also "
"by lowering the number of backend queries typically needed. Operators will "
"typically see PDNS taking less CPU and the backend seeing less load."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6545
msgid ""
"Furthermore, some real bugs were fixed. A couple of undocumented performance "
"switches may appear in --help output but you are advised to stay away from "
"these."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6549
msgid ""
"Developers: this version needs the pdns-2.5.1 development kit, available on "
"<ulink url=\"http://downloads.powerdns.com/releases/dev\"> "
"http://downloads.powerdns.com/releases/dev</ulink>. See also <xref "
"linkend=\"backend-writers-guide\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6557
msgid ""
"A big error in latency calculations - cached packets were weighed 50 times "
"less, leading to inflated latency reporting. Latency calculations are now "
"correct and way lower - often in the microseconds range."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6563
msgid ""
"It is now possible to run with 0 second cache TTLs. This used to cause very "
"frequent cache cleanups, leading to performance degradation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6569
msgid ""
"Many tiny performance improvements, removing duplicate cache key "
"calculations, etc. The cache itself has also been reworked to be more "
"efficient."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6575
msgid ""
"First 'CNAME' backend query replaced by an 'ANY' query, which most of the "
"time returns the actual record, preventing the need for a separate CNAME "
"lookup, halving query load."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6581
msgid "Much of the same for same-level-NS records on queries needing delegation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6591
msgid ""
"Incidentally, the cache count would show 'unknown' packets, which was "
"harmless but confusing. Thanks to Mike and Simon of NetNation for reporting "
"this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6597
msgid ""
"SOA hostmaster with a . in the local-part would be cached wrongly, leading "
"to a stray backslash in case of multiple successively SOA queries. Thanks to "
"Ascio Technologies for spotting this bug."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6603
msgid ""
"zone2sql did not parse Verisign zone files correctly as these contained a "
"$TTL statement in mid-record."
