#: docs/pdns.xml:6659
msgid ""
"An important release which has seen quite a lot of trial and error "
"testing. As a result, PDNS can now run with a huge cache and concurrent "
"invalidations. This is useful when running of a slower database or under "
"high traffic load with a fast database."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6663
msgid ""
"Furthermore, the gpgsql2 backend has been validated for use and will soon "
"supplant the gpgsql backend entirely. This also bodes well for the gmysql "
"backend which is the same code."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6667
msgid ""
"Also, a large amount of issues biting large scale slave operators were "
"addressed. Most of these issues would only show up after prolonged uptime."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6675
msgid ""
"Query cache. The old Packet Cache only cached entire questions and their "
"answers. This is very CPU efficient but does not lead to maximum "
"hitrate. Two packets both needing to resolve smtp.you.com internally would "
"not benefit from any caching. Furthermore, many different DNS queries lead "
"to the same backend queries, like 'SOA for .COM?'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6680
msgid ""
"PDNS now also caches backend queries, but only those having no answer (the "
"majority) and those having one answer (almost the rest)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6684
msgid ""
"In tests, these additional caches appear to halve the database backend load "
"numerically and perhaps even more in terms of CPU load. Often, queries with "
"no answer are more expensive than those having one."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6688
msgid ""
"The default <command>ttl</command>s for the query-cache and negquery-cache "
"are set to safe values (20 and 60 seconds respectively), you should be "
"seeing an improvement in behaviour without sacrificing a lot in terms of "
"quick updates."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6692
msgid "The webserver also displays the efficiency of the new Query Cache."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6695
msgid ""
"The old Packet Cache is still there (and useful) but see <xref "
"linkend=\"performance\"/> for more details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6700
msgid ""
"There is now the ability to shut off some logging at a very early "
"stage. High performance sites doing thousands of queries/second may in fact "
"spend most of their CPU time on attempting to write out logging, even though "
"it is ignored by syslog. The new flag <command>log-dns-details</command>, on "
"by default, allows the operator to kill most informative-only logging before "
"it takes any cpu."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6708
msgid ""
"Flags which can be switched 'on' and 'off' can now also be set to 'off' "
"instead of only to 'no' to turn them off."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6718
msgid ""
"Packet Cache is now case insensitive, leading to a higher hitrate because "
"identical queries only differing in case now both match. Care is taken to "
"restore the proper case in the answer sent out."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6724
msgid ""
"Packet Cache stores packets more efficiently now, savings are estimated at "
"50%."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6729
msgid ""
"The Packet Cache is now asynchronous which means that PDNS continues to "
"answer questions while the cache is busy being purged or "
"queried. Incidentally this will mean a cache miss where previously the "
"question would wait until the cache became available again."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6734
msgid ""
"The upshot of this is that operators can call <command>pdns_control "
"purge</command> as often as desired without fearing performance "
"loss. Especially the full, non-specific, purge was sped up tremendously."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6738
msgid ""
"This optimization is of little merit for small sites but is very important "
"when running with a large packetcache, such as when using recursion under "
"high load."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6744
msgid "AXFR log messages now all contain the word 'AXFR' to ease grepping."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6749
msgid ""
"Linux static version now compiled with gcc 3.2 which is known to output "
"better and faster code than the previously used 3.0.4."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6760
msgid ""
"Packetcache would sometimes send packets back with slightly modified flags "
"if these differed from the flags of the cached copy."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6766
msgid ""
"Resolver code did bad things with file descriptors leading to fd exhaustion "
"after prolonged uptimes and many slave SOA currency checks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6772
msgid ""
"Resolver code failed to properly log some errors, leading to operator "
"uncertainty regarding to AXFR problems with remote masters."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6778
msgid ""
"After prolonged uptime, slave code would try to use privileged ports for "
"originating queries, leading to bad replication efficiency."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6784
msgid ""
"Masters sending back answers in differing case from questions would lead to "
"bogus 'Master tried to sneak in out-of-zone data' errors and failing AXFRs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6791
msgid "Version 2.4"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6793 docs/pdns.xml:6864 docs/pdns.xml:6921
msgid ""
"Developers: this version is compatible with the pdns-2.1 development kit, "
"available on <ulink url=\"http://downloads.powerdns.com/releases/dev\"> "
"http://downloads.powerdns.com/releases/dev</ulink>. See also <xref "
"linkend=\"backend-writers-guide\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6797
msgid ""
"This version fixes some stability issues with malformed or malcrafted "
"packets. An upgrade is advised. Furthermore, there are interesting new "
"features."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6807
msgid ""
"Recursive queries are now also cached, but in a separate namespace so "
"non-recursive queries don't get recursed answers and vice versa. This should "
"mean way lower database load for sites running with the current default "
"lazy-recursion. Up to now, each and every recursive query would lead to a "
"large amount of SQL queries."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6812
msgid ""
"To prevent the packetcache from becoming huge, a separate "
"<command>recursive-cache-ttl</command> can be specified."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6817
msgid ""
"The ability to change parameters at runtime was added. Currently, only the "
"new <command>query-logging</command> flag can be changed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6823
msgid ""
"Added <command>query-logging</command> flag which hints a backend that it "
"should output a textual representation of queries it receives. Currently "
"only gmysql and gpgsql2 honor this flag."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6829
msgid ""
"Gmysql backend can now also talk to PgSQL, leading to less code. Currently, "
"the old postgresql driver ('gpgsql') is still the default, the new driver is "
"available as 'gpgsql2' and has the benefit that it does query logging. In "
"the future, gpgsql2 will become the default gpgsql driver."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6836
msgid ""
"DNS recursing proxy is now more verbose in logging odd events which may be "
"caused by buggy recursing backends."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6841
msgid "Webserver now displays peak queries/second 1 minute average."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6851
msgid ""
"Failure to connect to database in master/slave communicator thread could "
"lead to an unclean reload, fixed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6857
msgid ""
"Documentation: added details for <command>strict-rfc-axfrs</command>. This "
"feature can be used if very old clients need to be able to do zone transfers "
"with PDNS. Very slow."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6862
msgid "Version 2.3"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6868
msgid ""
"This release adds the Generic MySQL backend which allows full master/slave "
"semantics with MySQL and InnoDB tables (or other tables that support "
"transactions). See <xref linkend=\"generic-mypgsql-backends\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6872
msgid "Other new features:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6878
msgid ""
"Improved error messages in master/slave communicator will help down track "
"problems."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6883
msgid ""
"<command>slave-cycle-interval</command> setting added. Very large sites with "
"thousands of slave domains may need to raise this value above the default of "
"60. Every cycle, domains in indeterminate state are checked for their "
"condition. Depending on the health of the masters, this may entail many SOA "
"queries or attempted AXFRs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6897
msgid ""
"'pdns_control purge <userinput>domain</userinput>' and 'pdns_control purge "
"<userinput>domain$</userinput>' were broken in version 2.2 and did not in "
"fact purge the cache. There is a slight risk that domain-specific purge "
"commands could force a reload in previous version.  Thanks to Mike Benoit of "
"NetNation for discovering this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6904
msgid ""
"Master/slave communicator thread got confused in case of delayed answers "
"from slow masters. While not causing harm, this caused inefficient behaviour "
"when testing large amounts of slave domains because additional 'cycles' had "
"to pass before all domains would have their status ascertained."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6911
msgid ""
"Backends implementing special SOA semantics (currently only the undocumented "
"'pdns express backend', or homegrown backends) would under some "
"circumstances not answer the SOA record in case of an ANY query. This should "
"put an end to the last DENIC problems. Thanks to DENIC for helping us find "
"the problem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6919
msgid "Version 2.2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6925
msgid ""
"Again a big release. PowerDNS is seeing some larger deployments in more "
"demanding environments and these are helping shake out remaining issues, "
"especially with recursing backends."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6929
msgid ""
"The big news is that wildcard CNAMEs are now supported, an oft requested "
"feature and nearly the only part in which PDNS differed from BIND in "
"authoritative capabilities."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6933
msgid ""
"If you were seeing signal 6 errors in PDNS causing reloads and intermittent "
"service disruptions, please upgrade to this version."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6936
msgid ""
"For operators of PowerDNS Express trying to host .DE domains, the very "
"special <command>soa-serial-offset</command> feature has been added to "
"placate the new DENIC requirement that the SOA serial be at least six "
"digits. PowerDNS Express uses the SOA serial as an actual serial and not to "
"insert dates and hence often has single digit soa serial numbers, causing "
"big problems with .DE redelegations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6945
msgid ""
"Malformed or shortened TCP recursion queries would cause a signal 6 and a "
"reload. Same for EOF from the TCP recursing backend.  Thanks to Simon Kirby "
"and Mike Benoit of NetNation for helping debug this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6951
msgid ""
"Timeouts on the TCP recursing backend were far too long, leading to possible "
"exhaustion of TCP resolving threads."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6956
msgid ""
"<command>pdns_control purge domain</command> accidentally cleaned all "
"packets with that name as a prefix. Thanks to Simon Kirby for spotting this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6962
msgid ""
"Improved exception error logging - in some circumstances PDNS would not "
"properly log the cause of an exception, which hampered problem resolution."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6973
msgid "Wildcard CNAMEs now work as expected!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6978
msgid ""
"<command>pdns_control purge</command> can now also purge based on suffix, "
"allowing operators to purge an entire domain from the packet cache instead "
"of only specific records. See also <xref linkend=\"pdnscontrol\"/> Thanks to "
"Mike Benoit for this suggestion."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6985
msgid ""
"<command>soa-serial-offset</command> for installations with small SOA serial "
"numbers wishing to register .DE domains with DENIC which demands six-figure "
"SOA serial numbers. See also <xref linkend=\"all-settings\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6992
msgid "Version 2.1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6994
msgid ""
"This is a somewhat bigger release due to pressing demands from customers. An "
"upgrade is advised for installations using Recursion.  If you are using "
"recursion, it is vital that you are aware of changes in "
"semantics. Basically, local data will now override data in your recursing "
"backend under most circumstances. Old behaviour can be restored by turning "
"<command>lazy-recursion</command> off."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:6999
msgid ""
"Developers: this version has a new pdns-2.1 development kit, available on "
"<ulink url=\"http://downloads.powerdns.com/releases/dev\"> "
"http://downloads.powerdns.com/releases/dev</ulink>. See also <xref "
"linkend=\"backend-writers-guide\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7005
msgid ""
"Most users will run a static version of PDNS which has no dependencies on "
"external libraries. However, some may need to run the dynamic version.  This "
"warning applies to these users."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7009
msgid ""
"To run the dynamic version of PDNS, which is needed for backend drivers "
"which are only available in source form, gcc 3.0 is required.  RedHat 7.2 "
"comes with gcc 3.0 as an optional component, RedHat 7.3 does not. However, "
"the RedHat 7.2 Update gcc rpms install just fine on RedHat 7.3. For Debian, "
"we suggest running 'woody' and installing the g++-3.0 package. We expect to "
"release a FreeBSD dynamic version shortly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7022
msgid ""
"RPM releases sometimes overwrote previous configuration files. Thanks to "
"Jorn Ekkelenkamp of Hubris/ISP Services for reporting this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7027
msgid ""
"TCP recursion sent out overly large responses due to a byte order mistake, "
"confusing some clients.  Thanks to the capable engineers of NetNation for "
"bringing this to our attention."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7033
msgid ""
"TCP recursion in combination with a recursing backend on a non-standard port "
"did not work, leading to a non-functioning TCP listener. Thanks to the "
"capable engineers of NetNation for bringing this to our attention."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7040
msgid "Unexpected behaviour:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7044
msgid ""
"Wildcard URL records where not implemented because they are a performance "
"penalty. To turn these on, enable <command>wildcard-url</command> in the "
"configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7050
msgid ""
"Unlike other nameservers, local data did not override the internet for "
"recursing queries. This has mostly been brought into conformance with user "
"expectations. If a recursive question can be answered entirely from local "
"data, it is. To restore old behaviour, disable "
"<command>lazy-recursion</command>. Also see <xref linkend=\"recursion\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7062
msgid ""
"Oracle support has been tuned, leading to the first public release of the "
"Oracle backend. Zone2sql now outputs better SQL and the backend is now fully "
"documented. Furthermore, the queries are compatible with the PowerDNS "
"XML-RPC product, allowing PowerDNS express to run off Oracle. See <xref "
"linkend=\"oracle\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7069
msgid ""
"Zone2sql now accepts --transactions to wrap zones in a transaction for "
"PostgreSQL and Oracle output. This is a major speedup and also makes for "
"better isolation of inserts. See <xref linkend=\"zone2sql\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7075
msgid ""
"<command>pdns_control</command> now has the ability to purge the PowerDNS "
"cache or parts of it. This enables operators to raise the TTL of the Packet "
"Cache to huge values and only to invalidate the cache when changes are "
"made. See also <xref linkend=\"performance\"/> and <xref "
"linkend=\"pdnscontrol\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7083
msgid "Version 2.0.1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7085
msgid "Maintenance release, fixing three small issues."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7088 docs/pdns.xml:7117 docs/pdns.xml:7143 docs/pdns.xml:7228 docs/pdns.xml:7358
msgid "Developers: this version is compatible with 1.99.11 backends."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7094
msgid ""
"PowerDNS ignored the <command>logging-facility</command> setting unless it "
"was specified on the command line.  Thanks to Karl Obermayer from WebMachine "
"Technologies for noticing this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7100
msgid ""
"Zone2sql neglected to preserve 'slaveness' of domains when converting to the "
"slave capable PostgreSQL backend. Thanks to Mike Benoit of NetNation for "
"reporting this. Zone2sql now has a <command>--slave</command> option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7106
msgid ""
"SOA Hostmaster addresses with dots in them before the @-sign were "
"mis-encoded on the wire."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7112
msgid "Version 2.0"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7114
msgid "Two bugfixes, one stability/security related. No new features."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7126
msgid ""
"zone2sql refused to work under some circumstances, taking 100% cpu and not "
"functioning. Thanks to Andrew Clark and Mike Benoit for reporting this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7132
msgid ""
"Fixed a stability issue where malformed packets could force PDNS to "
"reload. Present in all earlier 2.0 versions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7138
msgid "Version 2.0 Release Candidate 2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7140
msgid "Mostly bugfixes, no really new features."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7152
msgid ""
"chroot() works again - 2.0rc1 silently refused to chroot. Thanks to Hub "
"Dohmen for noticing this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7157
msgid ""
"setuid() and setgid() security features were silently not being performed in "
"2.0rc1. Thanks to Hub Dohmen for noticing this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7162
msgid ""
"MX preferences over 255 now work as intended. Thanks to Jeff Crowe for "
"noticing this."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7167
msgid ""
"IPv6 clients can now also benefit from the recursing backend feature. Thanks "
"to Andy Furnell for proving beyond any doubt that this did not work."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7173
msgid ""
"Extremely bogus code removed from DNS notification reception code - please "
"test! Thanks to Jakub Jermar for working with us in figuring out just how "
"broken this was."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:7179
msgid ""
"AXFR code improved to handle more of the myriad different zone transfer "
"dialects available. Specifically, interoperability with Bind 4 was improved, "
"as well as Bind 8 in 'strict rfc conformance' mode. Thanks again for Jakub "
