#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:9699
msgid "Running PDNS on Microsoft Windows"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:9702
msgid ""
"If you installed pdns on Windows NT, 2000 or XP you can run pdns as a "
"service."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:9706
msgid ""
"This is how to do it: Go to services (<filename>Start->Settings->Control "
"Panel->Administrative Tools->Services</filename>) and locate "
"<filename>PDNS</filename> (you should have registered the program as a NT "
"service during the installation)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:9711
msgid ""
"Double-click on <filename>PDNS</filename> and push the start button. You "
"should now see a progress bar that gets to the end and see the status change "
"to 'Started'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:9715
msgid ""
"This is the same as starting pdns like this: <filename>pdns.exe "
"--ntservice</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:9720
msgid ""
"If you haven't registered pdns as a service during the installation you can "
"do so from the command line by starting pdns like this: <filename>pdns.exe "
"--register-service</filename>"
