#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10876
msgid ""
"Finally, two new tables are needed. DNSSEC keying material is stored in the "
"'cryptokeys' table (in a portable standard format).  Domain metadata is "
"stored in the 'domainmetadata' table. This includes NSEC3 settings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10880
msgid ""
"Once the database schema has been changed for DNSSEC usage (see the relevant "
"backend chapters or <ulink "
"url=\"http://wiki.powerdns.com/trac/wiki/PDNSSEC\">the PowerDNSSEC "
"wiki</ulink> for the update statements), the 'pdnssec' tool can be used to "
"fill out keying details, and 'rectify' the auth and ordername fields."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10884
msgid ""
"In short, 'pdnssec secure-zone powerdnssec.org ; pdnssec rectify-zone "
"powerdnssec.org' will deliver a correctly NSEC signed zone."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10887
msgid ""
"In addition, so will the 'zone2sql' import tool when run with the '--dnssec' "
"flag."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10890
msgid "From existing non-DNSSEC non-PowerDNS setups"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10891
msgid "TBD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10893
msgid "From existing DNSSEC non-PowerDNS setups, pre-signed"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10895
msgid ""
"Industry standard signed zones can be served natively by PowerDNS, without "
"changes. In such cases, signing happens externally to PowerDNS, possibly via "
"OpenDNSSEC, ldns-sign or dnssec-sign."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10899
msgid ""
"PowerDNS needs to know if a zone should receive DNSSEC processing. To "
"configure, run 'pdnssec set-presigned zone'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10901
msgid ""
"Right now, you will also need to configure NSEC(3) settings for pre-signed "
"zones using 'pdnssec set-nsec3'. Default is NSEC, in which case no further "
"configuration is necessary."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10904
msgid "From existing DNSSEC non-PowerDNS setups, live signing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10906
msgid ""
"The 'pdnssec' tool features the option to import zone keys in the industry "
"standard private key format, version 1.2. To import an existing KSK, use "
"'pdnssec import-zone-key zonename filename KSK', replace KSK by ZSK for a "
"Zone Signing Key."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10911
msgid ""
"If all keys are imported using this tool, a zone will serve mostly identical "
"records to before, with the important change that the RRSIG inception dates "
"will be different."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para><note><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10914
msgid ""
"Within PowerDNS, the 'algorithm' for RSASHA1 keys is modulated based on the "
"NSEC3 setting. So if an algorithm=7 key is imported in a zone with no "
"configured NSEC3, it will appear as algorithm 5!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10919
msgid "Records, Keys, signatures, hashes within PowerDNSSEC in online signing mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10921
msgid ""
"Within PowerDNSSEC live signing, keys are stored separately from the zone "
"records. Zone data are only combined with signatures and keys when requests "
"come in over the internet."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10925
msgid ""
"Each zone can have a number of keys associated with it, with varying key "
"lengths. Typically 1 or at most 2 of these keys are employed as actual Zone "
"Signing Keys (ZSKs). During normal operations, this means that only 1 ZSK is "
"'active', and the other is passive."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10930
msgid ""
"Should it be desired to 'roll over' to a new key, both keys can temporarily "
"be active (and used for signing), and after a while the old key can be "
"inactivated. Subsequently it can be removed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10934
msgid ""
"As elucidated above, there are several ways in which DNSSEC can deny the "
"existence of a record, and this setting too is stored away from zone "
"records, and lives with the DNSSEC keying material."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10938
msgid ""
"In order to facilitate interoperability with existing technologies, "
"PowerDNSSEC keys can be imported and exported in industry standard formats."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10941
msgid ""
"Keys and hashes are configured using the 'pdnssec' tool, which is described "
"next."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10943
msgid "(Hashed) Denial of Existence"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10945
msgid ""
"PowerDNS supports unhashed secure denial of existence using NSEC "
"records. These are generated with the help of the (database) backend, which "
"needs to be able to supply the 'previous' and 'next' records in canonical "
"ordering."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10950
msgid ""
"The Generic SQL Backends have fields that allow them to supply these "
"relative record names."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10953
msgid ""
"In addition, hashed secure denial of existence is supported using NSEC3 "
"records, in two modes, one with help from the database, the other with the "
"help of some additional calculations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10957
msgid ""
"NSEC3 in 'broad' or 'inclusive' mode works with the aid of the backend, "
"where the backend should be able to supply the previous and next domain "
"names in hashed order."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10961
msgid ""
"NSEC3 in 'narrow' mode uses additional hashing calculations to provide "
"hashed secure denial of existence 'on the fly', without further involving "
"the database."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10966
msgid "Signatures"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10968
msgid ""
"In PowerDNS live signing mode, signatures, as served through RRSIG records, "
"are calculated on the fly, and heavily cached. All CPU cores are used for "
"the calculation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10972
msgid ""
"RRSIGs have a validity period, in PowerDNS by default this period starts at "
"most a week in the past, and continues at least a week into the future."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10976
msgid ""
"Precisely speaking, the time period used is always from the start of the "
"previous Thursday until the Thursday two weeks later.  This two-week "
"interval jumps with one-week increments every Thursday."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para><note><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10979
msgid ""
"Why Thursday? POSIX-based operating systems count the time since GMT "
"midnight January 1st of 1970, which was a Thursday. PowerDNS "
"inception/expiration times are generated based on an integral number of "
"weeks having passed since the start of the 'epoch'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10987
msgid "'pdnssec' for PowerDNSSEC command &amp; control"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10989
msgid ""
"'pdnssec' is a powerful command that is the operator-friendly gateway into "
"PowerDNSSEC configuration. Behind the scenes, 'pdnssec' manipulates a "
"PowerDNS backend database, which also means that for many databases, "
"'pdnssec' can be run remotely, and can configure key material on different "
"servers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10994
msgid "The following pdnssec commands are available:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:10998
msgid "activate-zone-key ZONE KEY-ID"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11001
msgid "Activate a key with id KEY-ID within a zone called ZONE."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11006
msgid ""
"add-zone-key ZONE [ksk|zsk] [bits] "
"[rsasha1|rsasha256|rsasha512|gost|ecdsa256|ecdsa384]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11009
msgid ""
"Create a new key for zone ZONE, and make it a KSK or a ZSK, with the "
"specified algorithm."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11014
msgid "check-zone ZONE"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11017
msgid ""
"Check a zone for DNSSEC correctness. Main goals is to check if the auth flag "
"is set correctly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11022
msgid "check-all-zones"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11025
msgid "Check all zones for DNSSEC correctness. Added in 3.1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11030
msgid "deactivate-zone-key ZONE KEY-ID"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11033
msgid "Deactivate a key with id KEY-ID within a zone called ZONE."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11038
msgid "export-zone-dnskey ZONE KEY-ID"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11041
msgid ""
"Export to standard output DNSKEY and DS of key with key id KEY-ID within "
"zone called ZONE."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11046
msgid "export-zone-key ZONE KEY-ID"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11049
msgid ""
"Export to standard output full (private) key with key id KEY-ID within zone "
"called ZONE. The format used is compatible with BIND and NSD/LDNS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11055
msgid "hash-zone-record ZONE RECORDNAME"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11058
msgid ""
"This convenience command hashes the name 'recordname' according to the NSEC3 "
"settings of ZONE.  Refuses to hash for zones with no NSEC3 settings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11064
msgid "import-zone-key ZONE filename [ksk|zsk]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11067
msgid ""
"Import from 'filename' a full (private) key for zone called ZONE. The format "
"used is compatible with BIND and NSD/LDNS. KSK or ZSK specifies the flags "
"this key should have on import."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11074
msgid "import-zone-key-pem ZONE filename algorithm [ksk|zsk]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11077
msgid ""
"Import from 'filename' a full (private) key in PEM format for zone called "
"ZONE, and assign it an algorithm number. KSK or ZSK specifies the flags this "
"key should have on import. The format used is compatible with 'openssl "
"genrsa', which is also called PEM."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11085
msgid "rectify-zone ZONE [ZONE ..]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11088
msgid ""
"Calculates the 'ordername' and 'auth' fields for a zone called ZONE so they "
"comply with DNSSEC settings.  Can be used to fix up migrated data. Can "
"always safely be run, it does no harm. Multiple zones can be supplied."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11094
msgid "rectify-all-zones"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11097
msgid ""
"Do a rectify-zone for all the zones. Be careful when running this. Only bind "
"and gmysql backends are supported. Added in 3.1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11103
msgid "remove-zone-key ZONE KEY-ID"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11106
msgid "Remove a key with id KEY-ID from a zone called ZONE."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11111
msgid "secure-zone ZONE"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11114
msgid ""
"Configures a zone called ZONE with reasonable DNSSEC settings. You should "
"manually run 'rectify-zone' afterwards."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11119
msgid "set-nsec3 ZONE 'parameters' [narrow]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11122
msgid ""
"Sets NSEC3 parameters for this zone. A sample command line is: \"pdnssec "
"set-nsec3 powerdnssec.org '1 1 1 ab' narrow\".  The NSEC3 parameters must be "
"quoted on the command line."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11124 docs/pdns.xml:11151
msgid ""
"If running in RSASHA1 mode (algorithm 5 or 7), switching from NSEC to NSEC3 "
"will require a DS update at the parent zone!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11125
msgid ""
"The NSEC3 fields are: 'algorithm flags iterations salt'. Both 'algorithm' "
"and 'flags' should be 1 for PowerDNS operation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11131
msgid "set-presigned ZONE"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11134
msgid "Switches zone to presigned operation, utilizing in-zone RRSIGs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11139
msgid "show-zone ZONE"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11142
msgid "Shows all DNSSEC related settings of a zone called ZONE."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11147
msgid "unset-nsec3 ZONE"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11150
msgid "Converts a zone to NSEC operations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11156
msgid "unset-presigned ZONE"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11159
msgid "Disables presigned operation for ZONE."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11167
msgid "DNSSEC advice &amp; precautions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11169
msgid ""
"DNSSEC is a major change in the way DNS works. Furthermore, there is a "
"bewildering array of settings that can be configured."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11173
msgid ""
"It is well possible to configure DNSSEC in such a way that your domain will "
"not operate reliably, or even, at all."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11176
msgid ""
"We advise operators to stick to the keying defaults of 'pdnssec "
"secure-zone': RSASHA256 (algorithm 8), 1 Key Signing Key of 2048 bits, 1 "
"active Zone Signing Key of 1024 bits, 1 passive Zone Signing Key of 1024 "
"bits."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11180
msgid ""
"While the 'GOST' and 'ECDSA' algorithms are better choices in theory, not "
"many DNSSEC resolvers can validate answers signed with such keys. Much the "
"same goes for RSASHA512, except that it does not offer better performance "
"either."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><note><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11184
msgid ""
"GOST may be more widely available in Russia, because it might be mandatory "
"to implement this regional standard there."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11187
msgid ""
"It is possible to operate a zone with different keying algorithms "
"simultaneously, but it has also been observed that this is not reliable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11189
msgid "Packet sizes, fragments, TCP/IP service"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11191
msgid ""
"DNSSEC answers contain (bulky) keying material and signatures, and are "
"therefore a lot larger than regular DNS answers.  Normal DNS responses "
"almost always fit in the 'magical' 512 byte limit previously imposed on DNS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11195
msgid ""
"In order to support DNSSEC, operators must make sure that their network "
"allows for:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11197
msgid "&gt;512 byte UDP packets on port 53"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11198
msgid "Fragmented UDP packets"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11199
msgid "ICMP packets related to fragmentation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11200
msgid "TCP queries on port 53"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11201
msgid "EDNS0 queries/responses (filtered by some firewalls)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11205
msgid ""
"If any of the conditions outlined above is not met, DNSSEC service will "
"suffer or be completely unavailable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11208
msgid ""
"In addition, the larger your DNS answers, the more critical the above "
"becomes. It is therefore advised not to provision too many keys, or keys "
"that are unnecessarily large."
msgstr ""

