#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11426
msgid "TSIG: shared secret authorization and authentication"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><note><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11427
msgid "Available since PowerDNS Authoritative Server 3.0!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11429
msgid ""
"TSIG, as defined in RFC 2845, is a method for signing DNS messages using "
"shared secrets.  Each TSIG shared secret has a name, and PowerDNS can be "
"told to allow zone transfer of a domain if the request is signed with an "
"authorized name."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11434
msgid ""
"In PowerDNS, TSIG shared secrets are stored by the various backends. In case "
"of the popular Generic backends, they can be found in the 'tsigkeys' "
"table. The name can be chosen freely, but the algorithm name will typically "
"be 'hmac-md5'. The content is a Base64-encoded secret."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><note><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11439
msgid ""
"Most backends require DNSSEC support enabled to support TSIG. For the "
"Generic SQL Backend make sure to use the DNSSEC enabled schema and to turn "
"on the relevant '-dnssec' flag (for example, gmysql-dnssec)!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11441
msgid "Provisioning outbound AXFR access"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11443
msgid ""
"To actually provision a named secret permission to AXFR a zone, set a "
"metadata item in the 'domainmetadata' table called 'TSIG-ALLOW-AXFR' with "
"the key name in the content field."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><programlisting>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11449
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"sql> insert into tsigkeys (name, algorithm, secret) values ('test', "
"'hmac-md5', 'kp4/24gyYsEzbuTVJRUMoqGFmN3LYgVDzJ/3oRSP7ys=');\n"
"sql> select id from domains where name='powerdnssec.org';\n"
"5\n"
"sql> insert into domainmetadata (domain_id, kind, content) values (5, "
"'TSIG-ALLOW-AXFR', 'test');\n"
"\n"
"$ dig -t axfr powerdnssec.org @127.0.0.1 -y "
"'test:kp4/24gyYsEzbuTVJRUMoqGFmN3LYgVDzJ/3oRSP7ys='\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11447
msgid "As an example: <placeholder type=\"programlisting\" id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><programlisting>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11460
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"key test. {\n"
"        algorithm hmac-md5;\n"
"        secret \"kp4/24gyYsEzbuTVJRUMoqGFmN3LYgVDzJ/3oRSP7ys=\";\n"
"};\n"
"\n"
"zone \"powerdnssec.org\" {\n"
"\ttype master;\n"
"\tfile \"powerdnssec.org\";\n"
"\tallow-transfer {  key test.; };\n"
"};\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11458
msgid ""
"To ease interoperability, the equivalent configuration above in BIND would "
"look like this: <placeholder type=\"programlisting\" id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11473
msgid ""
"A packet authorized and authenticated by a TSIG signature will gain access "
"to a zone even if the remote IP address is not otherwise allowed to AXFR a "
"zone."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11477
msgid "Provisioning signed notification and AXFR requests"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11479
msgid ""
"To configure PowerDNS to send out TSIG signed AXFR requests for a zone to "
"its master(s), set the AXFR-MASTER-TSIG metadata item for the relevant "
"domain to the key that must be used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11483
msgid ""
"The actual TSIG key must also be provisioned, as outlined in the previous "
"section."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><programlisting>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11488
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"sql> insert into tsigkeys (name, algorithm, secret) values ('test', "
"'hmac-md5', 'kp4/24gyYsEzbuTVJRUMoqGFmN3LYgVDzJ/3oRSP7ys=');\n"
"sql> select id from domains where name='powerdnssec.org';\n"
"5\n"
"sql> insert into domainmetadata (domain_id, kind, content) values (5, "
"'AXFR-MASTER-TSIG', 'test');\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11486
msgid ""
"For the popular Generic SQL backends, configuring the use of TSIG for AXFR "
"requests could be achieved as follows: <placeholder type=\"programlisting\" "
"id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11495
msgid ""
"This setup corresponds to the TSIG-ALLOW-AXFR access rule defined in the "
"previous section."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para><programlisting>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11500
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"key test. {\n"
"        algorithm hmac-md5;\n"
"        secret \"kp4/24gyYsEzbuTVJRUMoqGFmN3LYgVDzJ/3oRSP7ys=\";\n"
"};\n"
"\n"
"server 127.0.0.1 {\n"
"        keys { test.; };\n"
"};\n"
"\n"
"zone \"powerdnssec.org\" {\n"
" type slave;\n"
" masters { 127.0.0.1; };\n"
" file \"powerdnssec.org\";\n"
"};\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11498
msgid ""
"In the interest of interoperability, the configuration above is (not quite) "
"similar to the following BIND statements: <placeholder "
"type=\"programlisting\" id=\"0\"/> Except that in this case, TSIG will be "
"used for all communications with the master, not just those about AXFR "
"requests."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11519
msgid "AXFR ACLs"
