#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11629
msgid "Recursion"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11630
msgid ""
"(only available from 1.99.8 and onwards, recursing component available since "
"2.9.5)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11632
msgid ""
"From 2.9.5 onwards, PowerDNS offers both authoritative nameserving "
"capabilities and a recursive nameserver component. These two halves are "
"normally separate but many users insist on combining both recursion and "
"authoritative service on one IP address. This can be likened to running "
"Apache and Squid both on port 80."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11637
msgid ""
"However, many sites want to do this anyhow and some with good reason. For "
"example, a setup like this allows the creation of fake domains which only "
"exist for local users. Such domains often don't end on \".com\" or \".org\" "
"but on \".intern\" or \".name-of-isp\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11641
msgid ""
"PowerDNS can cooperate with either its own recursor or any other you have "
"available to deliver recursive service on its port."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11644
msgid ""
"By specifying the <command>recursor</command> option in the configuration "
"file, questions requiring recursive treatment will be handed over to the IP "
"address specified. An example configuration might be "
"<command>recursor=130.161.180.1</command>, which designates 130.161.180.1 as "
"the nameserver to handle recursive queries."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11649
msgid ""
"Take care not to point <command>recursor</command> to the PowerDNS "
"Authoritative Server itself, which leads to a very tight packet loop!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11652 docs/pdns.xml:13339
msgid ""
"By specifying <command>allow-recursion</command>, recursion can be "
"restricted to netmasks specified. The default is to allow recursion from "
"everywhere. Example: <command>allow-recursion=192.168.0.0/24, 10.0.0.0/8, "
"1.2.3.4</command>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11655 docs/pdns.xml:12478
msgid "Details"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11657
msgid ""
"Questions carry a number of flags. One of these is called 'Recursion "
"Desired'. If PDNS is configured to allow recursion, AND such a flag is seen, "
"AND the IP address of the client is allowed to recurse via PDNS, then the "
"packet may be handed to the recursing backend."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11661
msgid ""
"If a Recursion Desired packet arrives and PDNS is configured to allow "
"recursion, but not to the IP address of the client, resolution will proceed "
"as if the RD flag were unset and the answer will indicate that recursion was "
"not available."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11665
msgid ""
"It is also possible to use a resolver living on a different port. To do so, "
"specify a recursor like this: "
"<command>recursor=130.161.180.1:5300</command>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11669
msgid ""
"If the backend does not answer a question within a large amount of time, "
"this is logged as 'Recursive query for remote 10.96.0.2 with internal id 0 "
"was not answered by backend within timeout, reusing id'. This may happen "
"when using 'BIND' as a recursor as it is prone to drop queries which it "
"can't answer immediately."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11674
msgid ""
"To make sure that the local authoritative database overrides recursive "
"information, PowerDNS first tries to answer a question from its own "
"database.  If that succeeds, the answer packet is sent back immediately "
"without involving the recursor in any way. This means that for questions for "
"which there is no answer, PowerDNS will consult the recursor for an "
"recursive query, even if PowerDNS is authoritative for a domain! This will "
"only cause problems if you 'fake' domains which don't really exist."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11678
msgid ""
"If you want to create such fake domains or override existing domains, please "
"set the <command>allow-recursion-override</command> feature (available from "
"2.9.14 until 2.9.22.6)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11681
msgid ""
"Some packets, like those asking for MX records which are needed for SMTP "
"transport of email, can be subject to 'additional processing'. This means "
"that a recursing nameserver is obliged to try to add A records (IP "
"addresses) for any of the mail servers mentioned in the packet, should it "
"have these addresses available."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11686
msgid ""
"If PowerDNS encounters records needing such processing and finds that it "
"does not have the data in its authoritative database, it will send an "
"opportunistic quick query to the recursing component to see if it perhaps "
"has such data. This question is worded such that the recursing nameserver "
"should return immediately such as not to block the authoritative nameserver."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11691
msgid ""
"This marks a change from pre-2.9.5 behaviour where a packet was handed "
"wholesale to the recursor in case it needed additional processing which "
"could not proceed from the authoritative database."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11696
msgid "PowerDNS Recursor: a high performance resolving nameserver"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11698
msgid ""
"The PowerDNS recursor is part of the source tarball of the main PowerDNS "
"distribution, but it is released separately. Starting from the version 3.0 "
"pre-releases, there are zero known bugs or issues with the recursor. It is "
"known to power the resolving needs of over 100 million internet connections."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11703
msgid ""
"The documentation below is only for the 3.0 series, users of older versions "
"are urged to upgrade!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11706
msgid "Notable features:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11709
msgid "Uses MTasker (<ulink url=\"http://ds9a.nl/mtasker\">homepage</ulink>)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11712
msgid ""
"Can handle thousands of concurrent questions. A quad Xeon 3GHz has been "
"measured functioning very well at 40000 real life replayed packets per "
"second, with 40% cpu idle. More testing equipment is needed to max out the "
"recursor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11716
msgid ""
"Powered by a highly modern DNS packet parser that should be resistant "
"against many forms of buffer overflows."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11719
msgid ""
"Best spoofing protection that we know about, involving both source port "
"randomisation and spoofing detection."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11722
msgid ""
"Uses 'connected' UDP sockets which allow the recursor to react quickly to "
"unreachable hosts or hosts for which the server is running, but the "
"nameserver is down. This makes the recursor faster to respond in case of "
"misconfigured domains, which are sadly very frequent."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11727
msgid ""
"Special support for FreeBSD, Linux and Solaris stateful multiplexing "
"(kqueue, epoll, completion ports, /dev/poll)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11730
msgid ""
"Very fast, and contains innovative query-throttling code to save time "
"talking to obsolete or broken nameservers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11733
msgid ""
"Code is written linearly, sequentially, which means that there are no "
"problems with 'query restart' or anything."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11736
msgid ""
"Relies heavily on Standard C++ Library infrastructure, which makes for "
"little code (406 core lines)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11739
msgid ""
"Is very verbose in showing how recursion actually works, when enabled to do "
"so with --verbose."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11742
msgid "The algorithm is simple and quite nifty."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11747
msgid ""
"The PowerDNS recursor is controlled and queried using the "
"<filename>rec_control</filename> tool."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11749
msgid "pdns_recursor settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11751
msgid ""
"At startup, the recursing nameserver reads the file "
"<filename>recursor.conf</filename> from the configuration directory, often "
"<filename>/etc/powerdns</filename> or "
"<filename>/usr/local/etc</filename>. Each setting below can appear on the "
"command line, prefixed by '--', or in the configuration file. The command "
"line overrides the configuration file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11756
msgid ""
"A switch can be set to on simply by passing it, like '--daemon', and turned "
"off explicitly by '--daemon=off' or '--daemon=no'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11762
msgid "aaaa-additional-processing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11765
msgid ""
"If turned on, the recursor will attempt to add AAAA IPv6 records to "
"questions for MX records and NS records.  Can be quite slow as absence of "
"these records in earlier answers does not guarantee their non-existence. Can "
"double the amount of queries needed. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11772
msgid "allow-from"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11775
msgid ""
"Comma separated netmasks (both IPv4 and IPv6) that are allowed to use the "
"server. The default allows access only from RFC 1918 private IP addresses, "
"like 10.0.0.0/8. Due to the aggressive nature of the internet these days, it "
"is highly recommended to not open up the recursor for the entire "
"internet. Questions from IP addresses not listed here are ignored and do not "
"get an answer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11783
msgid "allow-from-file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11786
msgid ""
"Like <command>allow-from</command>, except reading from file. Overrides the "
"'allow-from' setting.  To use this feature, supply one netmask per line, "
"with optional comments preceeded by a #.  Available since 3.1.5."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11794
msgid "auth-can-lower-ttl"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11797
msgid ""
"Authoritative zones can transmit a TTL value that is lower than that "
"specified in the parent zone. This is called a 'delegation "
"inconsistency'. To follow RFC 2181 paragraphs 5.2 and 5.4 to the letter, "
"enable this feature.  This will mean a slight deterioration of performance, "
"and it will not solve any problems, but does make the recursor more "
"standards compliant. Not recommended unless you have to tick an 'RFC 2181 "
"compliant' box. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11805
msgid "auth-zones"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11808
msgid ""
"Comma separated list of 'zonename=filename' pairs. Zones read from these "
"files are served authoritatively. Example: <command>auth-zones= "
"ds9a.nl=/var/zones/ds9a.nl, "
"powerdns.com=/var/zones/powerdns.com</command>. Available since 3.1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11813 docs/pdns.xml:14483
msgid "chroot"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11815 docs/pdns.xml:13357
msgid ""
"If set, chroot to this directory for more security. See <xref "
"linkend=\"security\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11818
msgid ""
"Make sure that <filename>/dev/log</filename> is available from within the "
"chroot. Logging will silently fail over time otherwise (on logrotate)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11822
msgid "client-tcp-timeout"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11825
msgid "Time to wait for data from TCP clients. Defaults to 2 seconds."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11830
msgid "config-dir"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11833
msgid "Directory where the configuration file can be found."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11838 docs/pdns.xml:14491
msgid "daemon"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11841
msgid "Operate in the background, which is the default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11846
msgid "delegation-only"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11849
msgid "A Verisign special."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11854
msgid "disable-packetcache"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11857
msgid ""
"Turn off the packet cache. Useful when running with Lua scripts that can not "
"be cached. Available since 3.2."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11862
msgid "dont-query"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11865
msgid ""
"The DNS is a public database, but sometimes contains delegations to private "
"IP addresses, like for example 127.0.0.1. This can have odd effects, "
"depending on your network, and may even be a security risk. Therefore, since "
"version 3.1.5, the PowerDNS recursor by default does not query private space "
"IP addresses. This setting can be used to expand or reduce the limitations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11872
msgid "entropy-source"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11875
msgid ""
"From version 3.1.5 onwards, PowerDNS can read entropy from a (hardware) "
"source. This is used for generating random numbers which are very hard to "
"predict. Generally on UNIX platforms, this source will be "
"<filename>/dev/urandom</filename>, which will always supply random numbers, "
"even if entropy is lacking.  Change to <filename>/dev/random</filename> if "
"PowerDNS should block waiting for enough entropy to arrive."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11883
msgid "export-etc-hosts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11886
msgid ""
"If set, this flag will export the host names and IP addresses mentioned in "
"<filename>/etc/hosts</filename>. Available since 3.1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11891
msgid "export-etc-hosts-suffix"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11894
msgid ""
"If set, all hostnames in the export-etc-hosts file are loaded in canonical "
"form, based on this suffix, unless the name contain a '.', in which case the "
"name is unchanged.  So an entry called 'pc' with "
"export-etc-hosts-suffix='home.com' will lead to the generation of "
"'pc.home.com' within the recursor.  An entry called 'server1.home' will be "
"stored as 'server1.home', regardless of the export-etc-hosts "
"setting. Available in since 3.4."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11908
msgid "fork"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11911
msgid ""
"If running on an SMP system with enough memory, this feature forks PowerDNS "
"so it benefits from two processors. Experimental. Renames controlsockets, so "
"care is needed to connect to the right one using "
"<command>rec_control</command>, using <command>--socket-pid</command>.  "
"Available in versions of the Recursor before 3.2, replaced by the 'threads' "
"setting."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11918
msgid "forward-zones"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11921
msgid ""
"Comma separated list of 'zonename=IP' pairs. Queries for zones listed here "
"will be forwarded to the IP address listed.  <command>forward-zones= "
"ds9a.nl=213.244.168.210, powerdns.com=127.0.0.1</command>. Available since "
"3.1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11925
msgid ""
"Since version 3.1.5, multiple IP addresses can be specified. Additionally, "
"port numbers other than 53 can be configured.  Sample syntax: "
"<command>forward-zones=ds9a.nl=213.244.168.210:5300;127.0.0.1, "
"powerdns.com=127.0.0.1;9.8.7.6:530</command>, or on the command line: "
"<command>--forward-zones=\"ds9a.nl=213.244.168.210:5300;127.0.0.1, "
"powerdns.com=127.0.0.1;9.8.7.6:530\"</command>,"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11930
msgid ""
"Forwarded queries have the 'recursion desired' bit set to 0, meaning that "
"this setting is intended to forward queries to authoritative servers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11935
msgid "forward-zones-file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11938
msgid ""
"Same as <command>forward-zones</command>, parsed from a file. Only 1 zone is "
"allowed per line, specified as follows: <command>ds9a.nl=213.244.168.210, "
"1.2.3.4:5300</command>. No comments are allowed. Available since 3.1.5."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11942
msgid ""
"Since 3.2, zones prefixed with a '+' are forwarded with the "
"recursion-desired bit set to one, for which see "
"'forward-zones-recurse'. Default behaviour without '+' is as with "
"'forward-zones'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11948
msgid "forward-zones-recurse"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11951
msgid ""
"Like regular 'forward-zones' (see above), but forwarded queries have the "
"'recursion desired' bit set to 1, meaning that this setting is intended to "
"forward queries to authoritative servers or to resolving servers. Available "
"since 3.2."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11957
msgid "hint-file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11960
msgid ""
"If set, the root-hints are read from this file. If unset, default root hints "
"are used. Available since 2.9.19."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11966
msgid "local-address"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11969
msgid ""
"Local IPv4 or IPv6 addresses to bind to, comma separated. Defaults to only "
"loopback. Addresses can also contain port numbers, for IPv4 specify like "
"this: <command>1.2.3.4:5300</command>, for IPv6: "
"<command>[::1]:5300</command>. Port specifications are available since "
"3.1.2."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11973
msgid ""
"When binding to wildcard addresses, UNIX semantics mean that answers may not "
"be sent from the address a query was received on. It is highly recommended "
"to bind to explicit addresses."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11979
msgid "local-port"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11982
msgid "Local port (singular) to bind to. Defaults to 53."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11988
msgid "log-common-errors"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11991
msgid ""
"Some DNS errors occur rather frequently and are no cause for alarm. Logging "
"these is on by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:11996
msgid "logging-facility"
msgstr ""

