"Place of this record. Defaults to 1, indicating 'Answer' section. Can also "
"be 2, for Authority of 3 for Additional.  When using this rare feature, "
"always emit records with 'Place' in ascending order. This field is usually "
"not needed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:12739
msgid "qname"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:12742
msgid ""
"qname of the answer, the 'name' of the record. Defaults to the name of the "
"query, which is almost always correct except when specifying additional "
"records or rolling out a CNAME chain."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:12748 docs/pdns.xml:15191
msgid "qtype"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:12751
msgid ""
"Currently the numerical qtype of the answer, defaulting to '1' which is an A "
"record. Can be also be specified as <function>pdns.A</function>, or "
"<function>pdns.CNAME</function> etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:12757 docs/pdns.xml:15175 docs/pdns.xml:15973 docs/pdns.xml:16045
msgid "ttl"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:12760
msgid ""
"Time to live of a record. Defaults to 3600. Be sure not to specify differing "
"TTLs within answers with an identical qname. While this will be encoded in "
"DNS, actual results may be undesired."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:12718
msgid ""
"Fields that can be set in the return table include: <placeholder "
"type=\"variablelist\" id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><warning><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:12770
msgid ""
"The result table must have indexes that start at 1! Otherwise the first or "
"confusingly the last entry of the table will be ignored. A useful technique "
"is to return data using: <literal>return 0, {{qtype=1, content=\"1.2.3.4\"}, "
"{qtype=1, content=\"4.3.2.1\"}}</literal> as this will get the numbering "
"right automatically."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:12778
msgid ""
"The function <function>matchnetmask(ip, netmask1, netmask2..)</function> (or "
"<function>matchnetmask(ip, {netmask1, netmask2})</function>) is available to "
"match incoming queries against a number of netmasks. If any of these match, "
"the function returns true."
