#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13692
msgid ""
"Besides counters, PDNS also maintains the ringbuffers. A ringbuffer records "
"events, each new event gets a place in the buffer until it is full. When "
"full, earlier entries get overwritten, hence the name 'ring'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13696
msgid ""
"By counting the entries in the buffer, statistics can be generated. These "
"statistics can currently only be viewed using the webserver and are in fact "
"not even collected without the webserver running."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13700
msgid "The following ringbuffers are available:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13705
msgid "Log messages (logmessages)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13706
msgid "All messages logged"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13709
msgid "Queries for existing records but for a type we don't have (noerror-queries)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13710
msgid ""
"Queries for, say, the AAAA record of a domain, when only an A is available.  "
"Queries are listed in the following format: name/type. So an AAA query for "
"pdns.powerdns.com looks like pdns.powerdns.com/AAAA."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13715
msgid "Queries for non-existing records within existing domains(nxdomain-queries)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13716
msgid ""
"If PDNS knows it is authoritative over a domain, and it sees a question for "
"a record in that domain that does not exist, it is able to send out an "
"authoritative 'no such domain' message. Indicates that hosts are trying to "
"connect to services really not in your zone."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13722
msgid "UDP queries received (udp-queries)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13724
msgid "All UDP queries seen."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13728
msgid "Remote server IP addresses (remotes)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13730
msgid ""
"Hosts querying PDNS. Be aware that UDP is anonymous - person A can send "
"queries that appear to be coming from person B."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13735
msgid "Remotes sending corrupt packets (remote-corrupts)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13737
msgid ""
"Hosts sending PDNS broken packets, possibly meant to disrupt service. Be "
"aware that UDP is anonymous - person A can send queries that appear to be "
"coming from person B."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13742
msgid "Remotes querying domains for which we are not auth (remote-unauth)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13744
msgid ""
"It may happen that there are misconfigured hosts on the internet which are "
"configured to think that a PDNS installation is in fact a resolving "
"nameserver. These hosts will not get useful answers from PDNS. This buffer "
"lists hosts sending queries for domains which PDNS does not know about."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13751
msgid "Queries that could not be answered due to backend errors (servfail-queries)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13753
msgid ""
"For one reason or another, a backend may be unable to extract answers for a "
"certain domain from its storage. This may be due to a corrupt database or to "
"inconsistent data. When this happens, PDNS sends out a 'servfail' packet "
"indicating that it was unable to answer the question. This buffer shows "
"which queries have been causing servfails."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13760
msgid "Queries for domains that we are not authoritative for (unauth-queries)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13762
msgid ""
"If a domain is delegated to a PDNS instance, but the backend is not made "
"aware of this fact, questions come in for which no answer is available, nor "
"is the authority. Use this ringbuffer to spot such queries."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13772
msgid "Supported record types and their storage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13774
msgid ""
"This chapter lists all record types PDNS supports, and how they are stored "
"in backends. The list is mostly alphabetical but some types are grouped."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13783
msgid "A"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13786
msgid ""
"The A record contains an IP address. It is stored as a decimal dotted quad "
"string, for example: '213.244.168.210'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13792
msgid "AAAA"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13795
msgid ""
"The AAAA record contains an IPv6 address. An example: "
"'3ffe:8114:2000:bf0::1'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13800
msgid "AFSDB (since 2.9.21)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13803
msgid ""
"Specialised record type for the 'Andrew Filesystem'. Stored as: '#subtype "
"hostname', where subtype is a number."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13808
msgid "CERT (since 2.9.21)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13811
msgid "Specialised record type for storing certificates, defined in RFC 2538."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13816
msgid "CNAME"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13819
msgid ""
"The CNAME record specifies the canonical name of a record. It is stored "
"plainly. Like all other records, it is not terminated by a dot. A sample "
"might be 'webserver-01.yourcompany.com'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13825
msgid "DNSKEY (since 2.9.21)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13828
msgid ""
"The DNSKEY DNSSEC record type is fully supported, as described in RFC "
"3757. Note that while PowerDNS can store, retrieve and serve DNSSEC records, "
"no further DNSSEC processing is performed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13834
msgid "DS (since 2.9.21)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13837
msgid ""
"The DS DNSSEC record type is fully supported, as described in RFC 3757. Note "
"that while PowerDNS can store, retrieve and serve DNSSEC records, no further "
"DNSSEC processing is performed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13843
msgid "HINFO"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13846
msgid ""
"Hardware Info record, used to specify CPU and operating system. Stored with "
"a single space separating these two, example: 'i386 Linux'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13852
msgid "KEY (since 2.9.21)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13855
msgid "The KEY record is fully supported. For its syntax, see RFC 2535."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13860
msgid "LOC"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13863
msgid ""
"The LOC record is fully supported. For its syntax, see RFC 1876. A sample "
"content would be: '51 56 0.123 N 5 54 0.000 E 4.00m 1.00m 10000.00m 10.00m'"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13868
msgid "MX"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13871
msgid ""
"The MX record specifies a mail exchanger host for a domain. Each mail "
"exchanger also has a priority or preference.  This should be specified in "
"the separate field dedicated for that purpose, often called 'prio'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13877
msgid "<anchor id=\"naptr\"/>NAPTR"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><screen>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13883
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t      '100  50  \"s\"  \"z3950+I2L+I2C\"     \"\"  "
"_z3950._tcp.gatech.edu'. \n"
"\t      "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13881
msgid ""
"Naming Authority Pointer, RFC 2915. Stored as follows: <placeholder "
"type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/> The fields are: order, preference, flags, "
"service, regex, replacement. Note that the replacement is not enclosed in "
"quotes, and should not be. The replacement may be omitted, in which case it "
"is empty. See also RFC 2916 for how to use NAPTR for ENUM (E.164) purposes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13892
msgid "NS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13895
msgid ""
"Nameserver record. Specifies nameservers for a domain. Stored plainly: "
"'ns1.powerdns.com', as always without a terminating dot."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13900
msgid "NSEC (since 2.9.21)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13903
msgid ""
"The NSEC DNSSEC record type is fully supported, as described in RFC "
"3757. Note that while PowerDNS can store, retrieve and serve DNSSEC records, "
"no further DNSSEC processing is performed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13909
msgid "PTR"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13912
msgid ""
"Reverse pointer, used to specify the host name belonging to an IP or IPv6 "
"address. Name is stored plainly: 'www.powerdns.com'.  As always, no "
"terminating dot."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13918
msgid "RP"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13921
msgid ""
"Responsible Person record, as described in RFC 1183. Stored with a single "
"space between the mailbox name and the more-information pointer. Example "
"'peter.powerdns.com peter.people.powerdns.com', to indicate that "
"peter@powerdns.com is responsible and that more information about peter is "
"available by querying the TXT record of peter.people.powerdns.com."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13928
msgid "RRSIG (since 2.9.21)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13931
msgid ""
"The RRSIG DNSSEC record type is fully supported, as described in RFC "
"3757. Note that while PowerDNS can store, retrieve and serve DNSSEC records, "
"no further DNSSEC processing is performed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13937
msgid "<anchor id=\"soa-type\"/>SOA"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13940
msgid ""
"The Start of Authority record is one of the most complex available. It "
"specifies a lot about a domain: the name of the master nameserver ('the "
"primary'), the hostmaster and a set of numbers indicating how the data in "
"this domain expires and how often it needs to be checked. Further more, it "
"contains a serial number which should rise on each change of the domain."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><screen>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13948
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t\tprimary hostmaster serial refresh retry expire default_ttl\n"
"\t      "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><table><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13952
msgid "SOA fields"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13956
msgid "primary"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13956
msgid "<command>default-soa-name</command> configuration option"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13959
msgid "hostmaster"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13959
msgid "hostmaster@domain-name"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13962 docs/pdns.xml:15786
msgid "serial"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13962
msgid "0"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13965 docs/pdns.xml:15776
msgid "refresh"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13965
msgid "10800 (3 hours)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13968
msgid "retry"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13968 docs/pdns.xml:13974
msgid "3600 (1 hour)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13971
msgid "expire"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13971
msgid "604800 (1 week)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13974
msgid "default_ttl"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13946
msgid ""
"The stored format is: <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/> Besides the "
"primary and the hostmaster, all fields are numerical. PDNS has a set of "
"default values: <placeholder type=\"table\" id=\"1\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13981
msgid ""
"The fields have complicated and sometimes controversial meanings. The "
"'serial' field is special. If left at 0, the default, PDNS will perform an "
"internal list of the domain to determine highest change_date field of all "
"records within the zone, and use that as the zone serial number. This means "
"that the serial number is always raised when changes are made to the zone, "
"as long as the change_date field is being set. Make sure to check whether "
"your backend of choice supports Autoserial."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13989
msgid "SPF (since 2.9.21)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13992
msgid "SPF records can be used to store Sender Policy Framework details (RFC 4408)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13997
msgid "SSHFP (since 2.9.21)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14000
msgid ""
"The SSHFP record type, used for storing Secure Shell (SSH) fingerprints, is "
"fully supported. A sample from RFC 4255 is: '2 1 "
"123456789abcdef67890123456789abcdef67890'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14006
msgid "SRV"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14009
msgid ""
"SRV records can be used to encode the location and port of services on a "
"domain name. When encoding, the priority field is used to encode the "
"priority. For example, '_ldap._tcp.dc._msdcs.conaxis.ch SRV 0 100 389 "
"mars.conaxis.ch' would be encoded with 0 in the priority field and '100 389 "
"mars.conaxis.ch' in the content field."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14016
msgid "TXT"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14019
msgid ""
"The TXT field can be used to attach textual data to a domain. Text is stored "
"plainly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:13780
msgid ""
"The PowerDNS Recursor can serve and store all record types, regardless of "
"whether these are explicitly supported.  <placeholder type=\"variablelist\" "
"id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

