#: docs/pdns.xml:14040
msgid ""
"More information about the PowerDNS community, and its mailing lists, can be "
"found on <ulink url=\"http://wiki.powerdns.com\">its Wiki</ulink>.  On the "
"wiki, you will also find information on how to file bugs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14044
msgid ""
"Below, please find a list of common questions asked on our public mailing "
"lists."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14048
msgid "Q: Help!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14051
msgid ""
"A: Please try harder :-) Specifically, before people will be able to help "
"you, they need to know a lot about your system. If you list more details, "
"chances are you'll get better answers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14057
msgid "Q: I have a question, what details should I supply?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14060
msgid ""
"A: Start out with stating what you think should be happening. Quite often, "
"wrong expectations are the actual problem.  Furthermore, which database "
"backend you use, your operating system, which version of PowerDNS you use "
"and where you got it from (RPM, .DEB, tar.gz). If you compiled it yourself, "
"what were the ./configure parameters."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14065
msgid ""
"If at *all* possible, supply the actual name of your domain and the IP "
"address of your server(s)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14071
msgid "Q: Where should I send my question?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14074
msgid ""
"A: To a mailing list. Please email the authors directly only if you "
"previously entered a support contract with them, or are considering doing "
"so.  For mailing list details, see <ulink "
"url=\"http://mailman.powerdns.com/mailman/admin/\">the mailing lists "
"page</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14079
msgid ""
"Questions about using PowerDNS should be sent to the pdns-users list, "
"questions about compiler errors or feature requests to pdns-dev."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14083
msgid "Before posting, read all FAQs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14088
msgid "Q: My information is confidential, must I send it to the mailing list?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14091
msgid ""
"If you desire privacy, please consider entering a support relationship with "
"us, in which case we invite you to contact "
"<email>powerdns.support.sales@netherlabs.eu</email>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14098
msgid "Using and Compiling PowerDNS FAQ"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14100
msgid ""
"In the course of compiling and using PowerDNS, many questions may "
"arise. Here are some we've heard earlier or questions we expect people may "
"have. Please read this list before mailing us!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14104
msgid ""
"If you don't see your question answered here, please check out <ulink "
"url=\"http://wiki.powerdns.com/projects/trac/wiki/TodoList\"> the Wiki "
"FAQ</ulink>, but do note that it is user-editable and not under our constant "
"control."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14110
msgid ""
"Q: I get this entry a lot of times in my log file: Authoritative empty NO "
"ERROR to 1.2.3.4 for 'powerdns.nl' (AAAA).."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14113
msgid ""
"As the name implies, this is not an error. It tells you there are questions "
"for a domain which exists in your database, but for which no record of the "
"requested type exists. To get rid of this error, add "
"<command>log-dns-details=off</command> to your configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14120
msgid "Q: Can I launch multiple backends simultaneously?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14123
msgid ""
"A: You can. This might for example be useful to keep an existing BIND "
"configuration around but to store new zones in, say MySQL. The syntax to use "
"is 'launch=bind,gmysql'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14129
msgid "Q: PowerDNS does not give authoritative answers, how come?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14132
msgid ""
"A: This is almost always not the case. An authoritative answer is recognized "
"by the 'AA' bit being set. Many tools prominently print the number of "
"Authority records included in an answer, leading users to conclude that the "
"absence or presence of these records indicates the authority of an "
"answer. This is not the case."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14137
msgid ""
"Verily, many misguided country code domain operators have fallen into this "
"trap and demand authority records, even though these are fluff and quite "
"often misleading. Invite such operators to look at section 6.2.1 of RFC "
"1034, which shows a correct authoritative answer without authority "
"records. In fact, none of the non-deprecated authoritative answers shown "
"have authority records!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14143
msgid ""
"Sorry for sounding like DJB on this, but we get so many misguided questions "
"about authority.."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14149
msgid "Q: Which backend should I use? There are so many!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14152
msgid ""
"A: If you have no external constraints, the Generic MySQL (gmysql) and "
"Generic PostgreSQL (gpgsql) ones are probably the most used and complete."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14156
msgid ""
"The Oracle backend also has happy users, we know of no deployments of the "
"DB2 backend. The BIND backend is pretty capable too in fact, but many prefer "
"a relational database."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14162
msgid "Q: I'm trying to build from SVN but I get lots of weird errors!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14165
msgid ""
"A: Read the 'HACKING' file, it lists the build requirements (mostly "
"autoconf, automake, libtool). In many cases, it may be easier to build from "
"the source distribution though. More information for developers is available "
"on <ulink url=\"http://wiki.powerdns.com\">the PowerDNS Open Source "
"Community Wiki</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14172
msgid ""
"Q: When compiling I get errors about 'sstream' and 'ostringstream', or "
"BITSPERCHAR"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14175
msgid ""
"A: Your gcc is too old. Versions 2.95.2 and older are not supported. Many "
"distributions have improved gcc 2.95.2 with an ostringstream implementation, "
"in which case their 2.95.2 is also supported."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14181
msgid "Q: PowerDNS crashes when I install the pdns-static .deb on Debian SID"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14184
msgid ""
"A: Indeed. Install the .deb files that come with Debian or recompile "
"PowerDNS yourself. If not using MySQL, the crashes will go away if you "
"remove setuid and setgid statements from the configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14190
msgid "Q: Why don't my slaves act on notifications and transfer my updated zone?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14193
msgid ""
"A: Raise the serial number of your zone. In most backends, this is the first "
"digit of the SOA contents field. If this number is lower to equal to that on "
"a slave, it will not consider your zone updated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14199
msgid "Q: Master or Slave support is not working, PDNS is not picking up changes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14202
msgid ""
"A: The Master/Slave apparatus is off by default. Turn it on by adding a "
"<command>slave</command> and/or <command>master</command> statement to the "
"configuration file. Also, check that the configured backend is master or "
"slave capable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14208
msgid ""
"Q: My masters won't allow PowerDNS to access zones as it is using the wrong "
"local IP address"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14211
msgid ""
"A: Mark Bergsma contributed the query-local-address setting to tell PowerDNS "
"which local IP address to use."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14216
msgid "Q: I compiled PowerDNS myself and I see weird problems, especially on SMP"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14219
msgid ""
"A: There are known issues between gcc &lt;3.2 and PowerDNS on Linux SMP "
"systems. The exact cause is not known but moving to our precompiled version "
"always fixes the problems. If you compile yourself, use a recent gcc!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14225
msgid ""
"Q: I see this a lot: Backend error: Failed to execute mysql_query, perhaps "
"connection died?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14228
msgid ""
"A: Check your MySQL timeout, it may be set too low. This can be changed in "
"the <filename>my.cnf</filename> file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14233
msgid ""
"Q: PowerDNS does not answer queries on all my IP addresses and I've ignored "
"the warning I got about that at startup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14236
msgid ""
"A: Please don't ignore what PowerDNS says to you. Furthermore, read <xref "
"linkend=\"all-settings\"/> about the <command>local-address</command> "
"setting, and use it to specify which IP addresses PowerDNS should listen on."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14242
msgid "Q: Can I use a MySQL database with the Windows version of PowerDNS?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14245
msgid ""
"A: You can. MySQL support is supplied through the ODBC backend, which is "
"compiled into the main binary.  So if you want to use MySQL you can change "
"the pdns.conf file, which is located in the PowerDNS for Windows directory, "
"to use the correct ODBC data sources.  If you don't know how to use ODBC "
"with MySQL:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14252
msgid ""
"Download MyODBC from <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.mysql.com/\">http://www.mysql.com/</ulink>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14255
msgid "Install the MySQL ODBC driver."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><note>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14258
msgid ""
"Then you can follow the instructions located in <xref "
"linkend=\"windows\"/>.  But instead of selecting the Microsoft Access Driver "
"you select the MySQL ODBC Driver and configure it to use your MySQL "
"database.  <note>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para><note><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14261
msgid ""
"For other databases for which an ODBC driver is available, the procedure is "
"the same as this example."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14268
msgid "Backend developer HOWTO"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14270
msgid ""
"Writing backends without access to the full PDNS source means that you need "
"to write code that can be loaded by PDNS at runtime.  This in turn means "
"that you need to use the same compiler that we do."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14274
msgid ""
"Furthermore, your pdns_server executable must be dynamically linked. The "
"default .rpm PDNS contains a static binary so you need to retrieve the "
"dynamic rpm or the dynamic tar.gz or the Debian unstable ('Woody') "
"deb. FreeBSD dynamic releases are forthcoming."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14279
msgid ""
"Q: Will PDNS drivers work with other PDNS versions than they were compiled "
"for?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14282
msgid ""
"A: 'Probably'. We make no guarantees. Efforts have been made to keep the "
"interface between the backend and PDNS as thin as possible. For example, a "
"backend compiled with the 1.99.11 backend development kit works with "
"1.99.10. But don't count on it.  We will notify when we think an "
"incompatible API change has occurred but you are best off recompiling your "
"driver for each new PDNS release."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14290
msgid "Q: What is in that DNSPacket * pointer passed to lookup!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14293
msgid ""
"A: For reasons outlined above, you should treat that pointer as opaque and "
"only access it via the <function>getRemote()</function> functions made "
"available and documented above. The DNSPacket class changes a lot and this "
"level of indirection allows for greater changes to be made without changing "
"the API to the backend coder."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14300
msgid "Q: How is the PowerDNS Open Source Backend Development Kit licensed?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14303
msgid "A: MIT X11, a very liberal license permitting basically everything."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14308
msgid "Q: Can I release the backend I wrote?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14311
msgid "A: Please do! If you tell us about it we will list you on our page."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14316
msgid "Q: Can I sell backends I wrote?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14319
msgid ""
"A: You can. Again, if you tell us about them we will list your backend on "
"the site. You can keep the source of your backend secret if you want, or you "
"can share it with the world under any license of your choosing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14325
msgid "Q: Will PowerDNS use my code in the PDNS distribution?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14328
msgid ""
"A: If your license permits it and we like your backend, we sure will.  If "
"your license does not permit it but we like your backend anyway we may "
"contact you."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14334
msgid ""
"Q: My backend compiles but when I try to load it, it says 'undefined symbol: "
"BackendMakers__Fv'"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14337
msgid ""
"A: You compiled with the wrong GCC. Use GCC 3.x for Linux, 2.95.x for "
"FreeBSD. You may want to change g++ to g++-3.0 in the Makefile, or change "
"your path so that 3.x is used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14343
msgid ""
"Q: I downloaded a dynamic copy of pdns_server but it doesn't run, even "
"without my backend"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14346
msgid ""
"A: Run 'ldd' on the pdns_server binary and figure out what libraries you are "
"missing. Most likely you need to install gcc 3.0 libraries, RedHat 7.1 and "
"7.2 have packages available, Debian installs these by default if you use the "
"'unstable deb' of PDNS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14352
msgid "Q: What is this 'AhuException' I keep reading about?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14355
msgid ""
"A: This name has historical reasons and has <ulink url=\"http://ds9a.nl\">no "
"significance</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14360
msgid "Q: I need a backend but I can't write it, can you help?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14363
msgid ""
"A: Yes, we also do custom development. Contact us at "
"powerdns.support.sales@netherlabs.eu, or visit <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.powerdns.com\">www.powerdns.com</ulink>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14371
msgid "About PowerDNS.COM BV, 'the company'"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14373
msgid ""
"As of 25 November 2002, the PowerDNS nameserver and its modules are open "
"source. This has led to a lot of questions on the future of both PowerDNS, "
"the company and the products. This FAQ attempts to address these questions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14379
msgid "Q: Is PowerDNS 2.9 really open source? What license?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14382
msgid ""
"A: PowerDNS 2.9 is licensed under the GNU General Public License version "
"two, the same license that covers the Linux kernel."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14387
msgid "Q: Is the open source version crippled?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14390
msgid "A: It is not. Not a single byte has been omitted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14395
msgid "Q: Is the nameserver abandoned?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14398
msgid ""
"A: Far from it. In fact, we expect development to speed up now that we have "
"joined the open source community."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14403
msgid "Q: Can I buy support contracts for PowerDNS?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14406
msgid "Sure, to do so, please contact us at <email>sales@powerdns.com</email>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14411
msgid "Q: Will you accept patches? We've added a feature"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14414
msgid ""
"Probably - in general, it is best to discuss your intentions and needs on "
"the <email>pdns-dev@mailman.powerdns.com</email> (<ulink "
"url=\"http://mailman.powerdns.com/mailman/listinfo/pdns-dev\">subscribe</ulink>)  "
"mailing list before doing the work. We may have suggestions or guidelines on "
"how you should implement the feature."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14421
msgid "Q: PowerDNS doesn't work on my platform, will you port it?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14422
msgid "Q: PowerDNS doesn't have feature I need, will you add it?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14425
msgid ""
"Be sure to ask on the <email>pdns-dev@mailman.powerdns.com</email> (<ulink "
"url=\"http://mailman.powerdns.com/mailman/listinfo/pdns-dev\">subscribe</ulink>) "
"mailing list. You can even hire us to do work on PowerDNS if plain asking is "
"not persuasive enough. This might be the case if we don't currently have "
"time for your feature, but you need it quickly anyhow, and are not in a "
"position to submit a patch implementing it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14432
msgid ""
"Q: Will <ulink url=\"http://express.powerdns.com\">PowerDNS Express</ulink> "
"be open sourced?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14435
msgid "Perhaps, we're not yet sure."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14441
msgid "Q: We are a Linux/Unix vendor, can we include PowerDNS?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14444
msgid ""
"A: Please do. In fact, we'd be very happy to work with you to make this "
"happen. Contact <email>ahu@ds9a.nl</email> if you have specific upstream "
"needs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14453
msgid "Other tools included with PowerDNS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14455
msgid ""
"PowerDNS comes with several tools that can be used to do various DNS related "
"things."
