#: docs/pdns.xml:14658
msgid "PipeBackend protocol"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14660
msgid ""
"Questions come in over a file descriptor, by default standard input. Answers "
"are sent out over another file descriptor, standard output by "
"default. Questions and answers are terminated by single newline ('\\n') "
"characters."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14665
msgid "Handshake"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:14667
msgid ""
"PowerDNS sends out 'HELO\\t1', indicating that it wants to speak the "
"protocol as defined in this document, version 1. For abi-version 2 or 3, "
"PowerDNS sends 'HELO\\t2' or 'HELO\\t3'.  A PowerDNS Coprocess must then "
"send out a banner, prefixed by 'OK\\t', indicating it launched "
"successfully. If it does not support the indicated version, it should "
"respond with FAIL, but not exit. Suggested behaviour is to try and read a "
"further line, and wait to be terminated."
msgstr ""

