"10.0.0.11 that list a NS record containing 'autoslave.powerdns.com' will "
"lead to the provisioning of a slave domain under the account 'internal'. See "
"<xref linkend=\"supermaster\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><para><programlisting>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15602
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t    insert into domains (name,type) values ('powerdns.com','MASTER');\n"
"\t  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15598
msgid ""
"The PostgreSQL backend is fully master capable with automatic discovery of "
"serial changes. Raising the serial number of a domain suffices to trigger "
"PDNS to send out notifications. To configure a domain for master operation "
"instead of the default native replication, issue: <placeholder "
"type=\"programlisting\" id=\"0\"/> Make sure that the assigned id in the "
"domains table matches the domain_id field in the records table!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15609
msgid "Oracle backend"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para><table><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15612
msgid "Oracle backend capabilities"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15621 docs/pdns.xml:15622
msgid "oracle"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15628
msgid ""
"This is the Oracle Database backend, completely rewritten for the 3.0 "
"release, with easily configurable SQL statements, allowing you to graft "
"PowerDNS functionality onto any Oracle database of your choosing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15633
msgid ""
"The Oracle backend is difficult, and possibly illegal, to distribute in "
"binary form. To use it, you will probably need to compile PowerDNS from "
"source. OCI headers are expected in "
"<filename>$ORACLE_HOME/rdbms/public</filename>, and OCI libraries in "
"<filename>$ORACLE_HOME/lib</filename>. That is where they should be with a "
"working installation of the full Oracle Database client. Oracle "
"InstantClient should work as well, but you will need to make the libraries "
"and headers available in appropriate paths."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15641
msgid ""
"This backend uses two kinds of database connections. First, it opens a "
"session pool.  Connections from this pool are used only for queries reading "
"DNS data from the database.  Second, it opens normal (non-pooled) "
"connections on demand for any kind of write access.  The reason for this "
"split is to allow redundancy by replication. Each DNS frontend server can "
"have a local read-only replicated instance of your database. Open the "
"session pool to the local replicated copy, and all data will be available "
"with high performance, even if the main database goes down. The writing "
"connections should go directly to the main database."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15651
msgid ""
"Of course, if you do not require this kind of redundancy, or want to avoid "
"the substantial Oracle Database licensing costs, all connections can just go "
"to the same database with the same credentials. Also, the write connections "
"should be entirely unnecessary if you do not plan to use either master or "
"slave mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15657
msgid "The following configuration settings are available:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15662
msgid "oracle-pool-database, oracle-pool-username, oracle-pool-password"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15665
msgid ""
"The database to use for read access. OracleBackend will try to create a "
"session pool, so make sure this database user has the necessary "
"permissions. If your connection requires environment variables to be set, "
"e.g.  <varname>ORACLE_HOME</varname>, <varname>NLS_LANG</varname>, or "
"<varname>LD_LIBRARY_PATH</varname>, make sure these are set when PowerDNS "
"runs.  <filename>/etc/default/pdns</filename> might help."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15675
msgid "oracle-master-database, oracle-master-username, oracle-master-password"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15678
msgid ""
"The database to use for write access. These are normal connections, not a "
"session pool. The backend may open more than one at a time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15684
msgid "oracle-session-min, oracle-session-max, oracle-session-inc"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15687
msgid ""
"Parameters for the connection pool underlying the session pool. OCI will "
"open <varname>session-min</varname> connections at startup, and open more "
"connections as needed, <varname>session-inc</varname> at a time, until "
"<varname>session-max</varname> connections are open."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15695
msgid "oracle-nameserver-name"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15698
msgid ""
"This can be set to an arbitrary string that will be made available in the "
"optional bind variable <varname>:nsname</varname> for all SQL statements.  "
"You can use this to run multiple PowerDNS instances off the same database, "
"while serving different zones."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15707
msgid ""
"There are many more options that are used to define the different SQL "
"statements. These will be discussed after the reference database schema has "
"been explained."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15711
msgid "The Database Schema"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15713
msgid ""
"You can find an example database schema in <filename>schema.sql</filename> "
"in the PowerDNS source distribution.  It is intended more as a starting "
"point to come up with a schema that works well for your organisation, than "
"as something you should run as it is. As long as the semantics of the SQL "
"statements still work out, you can store your DNS data any way you like."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15719
msgid ""
"You should read this while having <filename>schema.sql</filename> to "
"hand. Columns will not be specifically explained where their meaning is "
"obvious."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15724
msgid ""
"All FQDNs should be specified in lower case and without a trailing "
"dot. Where things are lexicographically compared or sorted, make sure a sane "
"ordering is used.  <userinput>NLS_LANG=AMERICAN_AMERICA.AL32UTF8</userinput> "
"should generally work well enough; when in doubt, enforce a plain ordering "
"with <userinput>NLSSORT(value, 'NLS_SORT = BINARY')</userinput>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15732
msgid "Zones Table"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15734
msgid ""
"This table lists the zones for which PowerDNS is supposed to be an "
"authoritative nameserver, plus a small amount of information related to "
"master/slave mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15742
msgid "The FQDN of the zone apex, e.g. <literal>example.com</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15747 docs/pdns.xml:15982 docs/pdns.xml:16053
msgid "type"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15750
msgid ""
"Describes how PowerDNS should host the zone. Valid values are "
"<constant>NATIVE</constant>, <constant>MASTER</constant>, and "
"<constant>SLAVE</constant>.  PowerDNS acts as an authoritative nameserver "
"for the zone in all modes. In slave mode, it will additionally attempt to "
"acquire the zone's content from a master server. In master mode, it will "
"additionally send <constant>NOTIFY</constant> packets to other nameservers "
"for the zone when its content changes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><tip><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15760
msgid ""
"There is a global setting to make PowerDNS send <constant>NOTIFY</constant> "
"packets in slave mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15767
msgid "last_check"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15770
msgid ""
"This value, updated by PowerDNS, is the unix timestamp of the last "
"successful attempt to check this zone for freshness on the master."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15779
msgid ""
"The number of seconds PowerDNS should wait after a successful freshness "
"check before performing another one. This value is also found in the zone's "
"SOA record. You may want to make sure to put the same thing in both places."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15789
msgid ""
"The serial of the version of the zone's content we are hosting now. This "
"value is also found in the zone's SOA record. You may want to make sure to "
"put the same thing in both places."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15796
msgid "notified_serial"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15799
msgid ""
"The latest serial for which we have sent <constant>NOTIFY</constant> "
"packets. Updated by PowerDNS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15814
msgid "The Zonemasters and ZoneAlsoNotify Tables"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15816
msgid ""
"These are lists of hosts PowerDNS will interact with for a zone in "
"master/slave mode.  <classname>Zonemasters</classname> lists the hosts "
"PowerDNS will attempt to pull zone transfers from, and accept "
"<constant>NOTIFY</constant> packets from.  "
"<classname>ZoneAlsoNotify</classname> lists hosts PowerDNS will send "
"<constant>NOTIFY</constant> packets to, in addition to any hosts that have "
"NS records."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15823
msgid ""
"Host entries can be IPv4 or IPv6 addresses, in string representation. If you "
"need to specify a port, use <userinput>1.2.3.4:5300</userinput> notation for "
"IPv4 and brackets for IPv6: <userinput>[abcd::1234]:5300</userinput>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15829
msgid "The Supermasters Table"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15831
msgid ""
"In superslave mode, PowerDNS can accept <constant>NOTIFY</constant> packets "
"for zones that have not been defined in the zone table yet. PowerDNS will "
"then create an entry for the zone and attempt a zone transfer. This table "
"defines the list of acceptable sources for supernotifications."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15841
msgid "An identifying string for this entry. Only used for logging."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15846
msgid "ip"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15849
msgid "The alleged originating IP address of the notification."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15854
msgid "nameserver"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15857
msgid "The FQDN of an authoritative nameserver."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15863
msgid ""
"A supernotification will be accepted if an entry is found such that the "
"notification came from <varname>ip</varname> and "
"<varname>nameserver</varname> appears in an NS record for that zone."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15868
msgid "The ZoneMetadata Table"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15870
msgid ""
"This is a per-zone key-value store for various things PowerDNS needs to know "
"that are not part of the zone's content or handled by other "
"tables. Depending on your needs, you may not want this to exist as an actual "
"table, but simulate this in PL/SQL instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15878
msgid "<constant>PRESIGNED</constant>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15881
msgid ""
"If set to 1, PowerDNS should assume that DNSSEC signatures for this zone "
"exist in the database and use them instead of signing records itself. For a "
"slave zone, this will also signal to the master that we want DNSSEC records "
"when attempting a zone transfer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15889
msgid "<constant>NSEC3PARAM</constant>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15892
msgid "The NSEC3 hashing parameters for the zone."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15897
msgid "<constant>TSIG-ALLOW-AXFR</constant>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15900
msgid ""
"The value is the name of a TSIG key. A client will be allowed to AXFR from "
"us if the request is signed with that key."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15906
msgid "<constant>AXFR-MASTER-TSIG</constant>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15909
msgid ""
"The value is the name of a TSIG key. Outgoing <constant>NOTIFY</constant> "
"packets for this zone will be signed with that key."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15875
msgid ""
"The currently defined metadata types are: <placeholder type=\"variablelist\" "
"id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15918
msgid "The Tables for Cryptographic Keys"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15920
msgid ""
"We have two of them: <classname>TSIGKeys</classname> for symmetric TSIG "
"keys, and <classname>ZoneDNSKeys</classname> for DNSSEC signing keys."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15925
msgid "The Records Table"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15927
msgid "The actual DNS zone contents are stored here."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15931 docs/pdns.xml:16069
msgid "zone_id"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15934
msgid ""
"The zone this records belongs to. Normally, this is obvious. When you are "
"dealing with zone delegations, you have to insert some records into the "
"parent zone of their actual zone. See also <varname>auth</varname>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15941 docs/pdns.xml:16037
msgid "fqdn"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15944
msgid ""
"The owner name of this record. Again, this is lower case and without a "
"trailing dot."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15949
msgid "revfqdn"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara><synopsis>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15954
#, no-wrap
msgid "'www.example.com' => 'com example www'"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15952
msgid ""
"This should be a string that consists of the labels of the owner name, in "
"reverse order, with spaces instead of dots separating them, for example: "
"<placeholder type=\"synopsis\" id=\"0\"/> This is used as a quick and dirty "
"way to get canonical zone ordering. You can chose a more correct and much "
"more complicated implementation instead if you prefer.  In the reference "
"schema, this is automatically set by a trigger."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15962
msgid "fqdnhash"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15965
msgid ""
"The NSEC3 hash of the owner name. The reference schema provides code and a "
"trigger to calculate this, but they are not production quality. The "
"recommendation is to load the dnsjava classes into your database and use "
"their facilities for dealing with DNS names and NSEC3 hashes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15976
msgid ""
"The TTL for the record set. This should be the same for all members of a "
"record set, but PowerDNS will quietly use the minimum if it encounters "
"different values."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15985
msgid ""
"The type of the record, as a canonical identification string, e.g.  "
"<constant>AAAA</constant> or <constant>MX</constant>. You can set this and "
"<varname>content</varname> NULL to indicate a name that exists, but doesn't "
"carry any record (a so called empty non-terminal) for NSEC/NSEC3 ordering "
"purposes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:15996
msgid ""
"The data part of the DNS record, in canonical string representation, except "
"that if this includes FQDNs, they should be specified without a trailing "
"dot."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:16002 docs/pdns.xml:16078
msgid "last_change"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:16005
msgid ""
"The unix timestamp of the last change to this record. Used only for the "
"deprecated autoserial feature. You can omit this unless you want to use that "
"feature."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: docs/pdns.xml:16011 docs/pdns.xml:16087
msgid "auth"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:16014
msgid ""
"0 or 1 depending on whether this record is an authoritative member of the "
"zone specified in <varname>zone_id</varname>. These are the rules for "
"determining that: A record is an authoritative member of the zone its owner "
"name belongs to, except for DS records, which are authoritative members of "
"the parent zone. Delegation records, that is, NS records and related A/AAAA "
"glue records, are additionally non-authoritative members of the parent zone."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:16022
msgid ""
"PowerDNS has a function to automatically set this. OracleBackend doesn't "
"support that.  Do it in the database."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:16031
msgid "The SQL Statements"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:16032
msgid "Fetching DNS records"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:16040
msgid "The owner name of the record."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:16048
msgid "The TTL of the record set."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:16056
msgid "The type of the record."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:16064
msgid "The content of the record."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:16072
msgid ""
"The numerical identifier of the zone the record belongs to. A record can "
"belong to two zones (delegations/glue), in which case it may be returned "
"twice."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:16081
msgid ""
"The unix timestamp of the last time this record was changed. Can safely be "
"set as a constant 0, unless you use the autoserial feature."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><simpara>
#: docs/pdns.xml:16090
msgid "1 or 0 depending on the zone membership (authoritative or not)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:16034
msgid ""
"There are five queries to do this. They all share the same set of return "
"columns: <placeholder type=\"variablelist\" id=\"0\"/> Record sets (records "
"for the same name of the same type) must appear consecutively, which means "
"<command>ORDER BY</command> clauses are needed in some places. Empty "
"non-terminals should be suppressed."
msgstr ""

