#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18320
msgid "Compiling PowerDNS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18321
msgid "Compiling PowerDNS on Unix"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para><note><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18324
msgid ""
"For now, see <ulink url=\"http://wiki.powerdns.com/\">the Open Source "
"PowerDNS site</ulink>.  <command>./configure ; make ; make install</command> "
"will do The Right Thing for most people."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18329
msgid ""
"PowerDNS can be compiled with modules built in, or with modules designed to "
"be loaded at runtime. All that is configured before compiling using the well "
"known autoconf/automake system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18333
msgid ""
"To compile in modules, specify them as <command>--with-modules=\"mod1 mod2 "
"mod3\"</command>, substituting the desired module names.  Each backend has a "
"module name in the table at the beginning of its section."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18337
msgid ""
"To compile a module for inclusion at runtime, which is great if you are a "
"unix vendor, use <command>--with-dynmodules=\"mod1 mod2 mod3\"</command>.  "
"These modules then end up as .so files in the compiled libdir."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18341
msgid ""
"Starting with version 2.9.18, PowerDNS requires 'Boost' to compile, it is "
"available for most operating systems. Otherwise, see <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.boost.org\">the Boost website</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18344
msgid "AIX"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18346
msgid ""
"Known to compile with gcc, but only since 2.9.8. AIX lacks POSIX semaphores "
"so they need to be emulated, as with MacOS X."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18349
msgid "FreeBSD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18351
msgid ""
"Works fine, but use gmake. Pipe backend is currently broken, for reasons, "
"see <xref linkend=\"pipebackend\"/>. Due to the threading model of FreeBSD, "
"PowerDNS does not benefit from additional CPUs on the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18355
msgid ""
"The FreeBSD Boost include files are installed in "
"<filename>/usr/local/include</filename>, so prefix "
"<command>CXXFLAGS=-I/usr/local/include</command> to your "
"<command>./configure</command> invocation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18359
msgid "Linux"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18361
msgid ""
"Linux is probably the best supported platform as most of the main coders are "
"Linux users. The static DEB distribution is known to have problems on Debian "
"'Sid', but that doesn't matter as PowerDNS is a native part of Debian "
"'Sid'. Just apt-get!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18365
msgid "MacOS X"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18367
msgid ""
"Did compile at one point but maintenance has lapsed. Let us know if you can "
"provide us with a login on MacOS X or if you want to help."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18370
msgid "OpenBSD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18372
msgid ""
"Compiles but then does not work very well. We hear that it may work with "
"more recent versions of gcc, please let us know on "
"<email>pdns-dev@mailman.powerdns.com</email>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><title>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18376
msgid "Solaris"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18378
msgid ""
"Solaris 7 is supported, but only just. AAAA records do not work on Solaris "
"7. Solaris 8 and 9 work fine. The 'Sunpro' compiler has not been tried but "
"is reported to be lacking large parts of the Standard Template Library, "
"which PowerDNS relies on heavily.  Use gcc and gmake (if available). Regular "
"Solaris make has some issues with some PowerDNS Makefile constructs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <book><appendix><sect1><sect2><para>
#: docs/pdns.xml:18383
msgid ""
"When compiling, make sure that you have <filename>/usr/ccs/bin</filename> in "
"your path. Furthermore, with some versions of MySQL, you may have to add "
"\"LDFLAGS=-lz\" before <command>./configure</command>."
msgstr ""

